ihohum.wordpress.com/2012/09/14/hello-world/','Uncategorized;Oped12',NULL,NULL,25,NULL,NULL,NULL,43,'For an e-learning professional (and fairly extroverted character f2f) I confess to having a rather introverted online persona. Â Well this clearly has to change and so I have Â started this blog &#8211; prompted by having just embarked on the Openness &#8230; <a href=\"http://feefihohum.wordpress.com/2012/09/14/hello-world/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=feefihohum.wordpress.com&#038;blog=40457811&#038;post=1&#038;subd=feefihohum&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1347894604,NULL,NULL,'feefihohum','http://feefihohum.wordpress.com','Fri, 14 Sep 2012 14:19:31 +0000',NULL,'feefihohum',NULL,'<p>For an e-learning professional (and fairly extroverted character f2f) I confess to having a rather introverted online persona. Â Well this clearly has to change and so I have Â started this blog &#8211; prompted by having just embarked on the Openness in Education MOOC.</p>\n<p>Watched the helpfulÂ <a href=\"http://feefihohum.wordpress.com/2012/09/14/hello-world/\"><img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/eW3gMGqcZQc/2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a>Â from Dave Cormier and must commit myself to:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>OrientÂ myself (still in the middle of this)</li>\n<li>Declare myself (not quite ready &#8211; but this blog is part of that)</li>\n<li>Network &#8211; need to find the other learners &#8211; how many of us are there? who are they? where are they?</li>\n<li>Cluster &#8211; i read this as &#8216;make a clique&#8230;&#8217;</li>\n<li>Focus. Â Indeed.</li>\n</ol>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/feefihohum.wordpress.com/1/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/feefihohum.wordpress.com/1/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=feefihohum.wordpress.com&#038;blog=40457811&#038;post=1&#038;subd=feefihohum&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(350,13,0,'Course Started','text/html','http://openedmooc.blogspot.com/2012/09/this-blog-is-created-for-course.html','#oped12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-14 19:28:42',44,'This blog is created for the course discussion at Open Education MOOC (massive open online course).<img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/6717987710670160250-5546499681046819867?l=openedmooc.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1347894724,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 13 Sep 2012 05:53:00 +0000',NULL,'Open Education','13','This blog is created for the course discussion at Open Education MOOC (massive open online course).<img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/6717987710670160250-5546499681046819867?l=openedmooc.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(351,0,0,'Learning to Love Google+','text/html','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/2012/09/learning-to-love-google.html','Google Plus',NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-12 16:20:08',19,'<a href=\"http://www.marketingprofessor.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-tips.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"200\" src=\"http://www.marketingprofessor.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-tips.jpg\" width=\"200\" /></a>I&apos;ve tried and I&apos;ve tried and I&apos;ve tried - really I have! And I still don&apos;t quite get it. I&apos;m not alone either - using my <a href=\"http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.co.uk/2012/07/power-searching-with-google.html\">newly-found search skills</a>, I got rid of some earlier grumbles and found <a href=\"http://www.sitepronews.com/2012/08/21/google-the-next-big-thing-or-another-google-failure/\">a thoughtful but fairly negative piece</a> posted within the last month (balanced by the comments, which are well worth reading btw).<br /><br />However, never say never, and I do use the amazing Hangouts video feature and more&apos;s to the point here, my <a href=\"http://www.hillbrent.co.uk/\">most esteemed and clever friend</a> uses Hangouts for all kinds of business meetings a lot of the time and mentioned in passing how people still find it quite difficult to use, even though the technology itself is remarkably user-friendly. Which is when I offered to write something to try to help, as I envisage using it more myself...<br /><br />So, I&apos;m declaring my intentions here and have begun to sketch out the different sections of a Wonderful Guide to Google+ - an introduction, an overview, how to get started, using the main features - that kind of does it for now. At some point soonish, I&apos;ll produce a complete guide, but in the meantime, I&apos;ll post the various sections here, starting with a very brief...<br /><h2>Introduction to Google+</h2>Google+ (or &apos;Google Plus&apos;) is Google&apos;s very own social networking product â€“ their answer to Twitter and Facebook.&amp;nbsp;<br /><b>What Google+ does well</b>: it&apos;s nice to be able to put people into groups that you control and the privacy settings are also more nuanced (than Facebook, say) â€“ and if you&apos;re a Google mail and calendar and blogs and all user, then integration is very useful. &amp;nbsp;Best of all is Hangouts, the video chat feature, which is very user-friendly.&amp;nbsp;<br /><b>Where it becomes tricky</b>: in all honesty, there&apos;s quite a lot going on here and it can come across as complicated â€“ which, of course, is off-putting for most of us!<br />However, having spent just a little time with it, I can tell you that I think it&apos;s worth getting to grips with for all the advantages â€“ and that&apos;s why I&apos;ve put this document together, because the idea here is to lead you slowly through the main aspects of Google+ so that you can then develop your own way of using it.&amp;nbsp;<br />(that last paragraph may become darker if I still don&apos;t get it by the end of the document!)<img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-1196411249256333943?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1347894963,NULL,NULL,'Bill Miller','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/','2012-09-12T16:20:00.000+01:00',NULL,'As Wonderful As Sunsets',NULL,'<a href=\"http://www.marketingprofessor.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-tips.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"200\" src=\"http://www.marketingprofessor.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-tips.jpg\" width=\"200\" /></a>I&apos;ve tried and I&apos;ve tried and I&apos;ve tried - really I have! And I still don&apos;t quite get it. I&apos;m not alone either - using my <a href=\"http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.co.uk/2012/07/power-searching-with-google.html\">newly-found search skills</a>, I got rid of some earlier grumbles and found <a href=\"http://www.sitepronews.com/2012/08/21/google-the-next-big-thing-or-another-google-failure/\">a thoughtful but fairly negative piece</a> posted within the last month (balanced by the comments, which are well worth reading btw).<br /><br />However, never say never, and I do use the amazing Hangouts video feature and more&apos;s to the point here, my <a href=\"http://www.hillbrent.co.uk/\">most esteemed and clever friend</a> uses Hangouts for all kinds of business meetings a lot of the time and mentioned in passing how people still find it quite difficult to use, even though the technology itself is remarkably user-friendly. Which is when I offered to write something to try to help, as I envisage using it more myself...<br /><br />So, I&apos;m declaring my intentions here and have begun to sketch out the different sections of a Wonderful Guide to Google+ - an introduction, an overview, how to get started, using the main features - that kind of does it for now. At some point soonish, I&apos;ll produce a complete guide, but in the meantime, I&apos;ll post the various sections here, starting with a very brief...<br /><h2>Introduction to Google+</h2>Google+ (or &apos;Google Plus&apos;) is Google&apos;s very own social networking product â€“ their answer to Twitter and Facebook.&amp;nbsp;<br /><b>What Google+ does well</b>: it&apos;s nice to be able to put people into groups that you control and the privacy settings are also more nuanced (than Facebook, say) â€“ and if you&apos;re a Google mail and calendar and blogs and all user, then integration is very useful. &amp;nbsp;Best of all is Hangouts, the video chat feature, which is very user-friendly.&amp;nbsp;<br /><b>Where it becomes tricky</b>: in all honesty, there&apos;s quite a lot going on here and it can come across as complicated â€“ which, of course, is off-putting for most of us!<br />However, having spent just a little time with it, I can tell you that I think it&apos;s worth getting to grips with for all the advantages â€“ and that&apos;s why I&apos;ve put this document together, because the idea here is to lead you slowly through the main aspects of Google+ so that you can then develop your own way of using it.&amp;nbsp;<br />(that last paragraph may become darker if I still don&apos;t get it by the end of the document!)<img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-1196411249256333943?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(352,0,0,'Embedding a video you can size on Google Sites - and the joy of helpful people','text/html','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/2012/09/embedding-video-you-can-size-on-google.html','youtube',NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-12 12:14:51',19,'On my <a href=\"http://www.wonderful-learning.com/\">new website</a> I created a video to personalise the site and to better explain my aims. I had worked out that if I hosted said video in Google Docs (now Drive), then I wouldn&apos;t have to show all the YouTube&amp;nbsp;paraphernalia&amp;nbsp;and, more importantly, I would be able to make it a more aesthetically pleasing size (and not the slightly too-big look of&amp;nbsp;straightforward&amp;nbsp;YouTube embedding...). So, I duly made the vid and was reasonably pleased with the quality and the performance - I embedded it on the main page and thought that was that - but <a href=\"http://ojmason.net/\">my Twitter friend</a> informed me that the Vid couldn&apos;t be played on Apple kit - no flash, apparently. Bugger. I quickly found an appropriate Google Group and was, over time, very gently helped towards a solution, which involves using <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/annuairevin/inserting-youtube-player\">a Google Gadget</a>, which will take the YouTube embed code and allow you to size it in Sites.<br /><br />I&apos;m really happy to have been able to do this, but more than that, I&apos;m really pleased there are such amazing people as Prac to keep visiting the Google Group and help people out. He has <a href=\"https://plus.google.com/115854656993758258488/about\">some great pages</a> around and about and here&apos;s his <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/annuairevin/tips-and-tricks-for-google-sites\">Tips and Tricks for Google Sites</a>.<br /><br />A noteworthy mention to Stephen from&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.steegle.com/\">www.steegle.com</a>&amp;nbsp;too - I&apos;d found the solution by the time he chipped in, but how brilliant that he did - Steegle&apos;s a great site, by the way, well worth a visit!<br /><br />Have a look at the video in context - what do you think? (and does it still work with Apple? It should, I tested it, but you never know, perhaps I&apos;m just too anxious after all this and should just trust the tech...):&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wonderful-learning.com/\">www.wonderful-learning.com</a><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-7104904918164379505?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1347894963,NULL,NULL,'Bill Miller','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/','2012-09-12T12:14:00.003+01:00',NULL,'As Wonderful As Sunsets',NULL,'On my <a href=\"http://www.wonderful-learning.com/\">new website</a> I created a video to personalise the site and to better explain my aims. I had worked out that if I hosted said video in Google Docs (now Drive), then I wouldn&apos;t have to show all the YouTube&amp;nbsp;paraphernalia&amp;nbsp;and, more importantly, I would be able to make it a more aesthetically pleasing size (and not the slightly too-big look of&amp;nbsp;straightforward&amp;nbsp;YouTube embedding...). So, I duly made the vid and was reasonably pleased with the quality and the performance - I embedded it on the main page and thought that was that - but <a href=\"http://ojmason.net/\">my Twitter friend</a> informed me that the Vid couldn&apos;t be played on Apple kit - no flash, apparently. Bugger. I quickly found an appropriate Google Group and was, over time, very gently helped towards a solution, which involves using <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/annuairevin/inserting-youtube-player\">a Google Gadget</a>, which will take the YouTube embed code and allow you to size it in Sites.<br /><br />I&apos;m really happy to have been able to do this, but more than that, I&apos;m really pleased there are such amazing people as Prac to keep visiting the Google Group and help people out. He has <a href=\"https://plus.google.com/115854656993758258488/about\">some great pages</a> around and about and here&apos;s his <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/annuairevin/tips-and-tricks-for-google-sites\">Tips and Tricks for Google Sites</a>.<br /><br />A noteworthy mention to Stephen from&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.steegle.com/\">www.steegle.com</a>&amp;nbsp;too - I&apos;d found the solution by the time he chipped in, but how brilliant that he did - Steegle&apos;s a great site, by the way, well worth a visit!<br /><br />Have a look at the video in context - what do you think? (and does it still work with Apple? It should, I tested it, but you never know, perhaps I&apos;m just too anxious after all this and should just trust the tech...):&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wonderful-learning.com/\">www.wonderful-learning.com</a><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-7104904918164379505?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(353,23,0,'Opennes in Educaton &#8211; Motivation &#8211; Week 1','text/html','http://filosofiadebolsillo.wordpress.com/2012/09/11/opennes-in-educaton-motivation-week-1/','EducaciÃ³n;MOOC;TIC;#oped12;moocmooc;Week 1',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'Yesterday morning I received the kick off mail for the course Open Education, facilitate by George SiemensÂ and Rory McGreal. You can find the course schedule here, it will go from the Open Definition to the Open Teaching. Because I very motivated to learn about MOOC&#8217;s, specially learning about teaching, I decided to do one full &#8230; <a href=\"http://filosofiadebolsillo.wordpress.com/2012/09/11/opennes-in-educaton-motivation-week-1/\">Continuar leyendo &#187;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=filosofiadebolsillo.wordpress.com&#038;blog=28508677&#038;post=853&#038;subd=filosofiadebolsillo&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1347895084,NULL,NULL,'FilodeBolsillo','http://filosofiadebolsillo.wordpress.com','Tue, 11 Sep 2012 16:09:00 +0000',NULL,'FilosofÃ­a de Bolsillo','23','<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Yesterday morning I received the kick off mail for the course <em>Open Education, </em>facilitate by <a title=\"George Siemens\" href=\"http://scis.athabascau.ca/scis/staff/showStaffInfo.php?ct=siemens\" target=\"_blank\">George Siemens</a>Â and <a title=\"Rory McGreal\" href=\"https://unescochair.athabascau.ca/team/chairholder\" target=\"_blank\">Rory McGreal</a>. You can find the course schedule <em><a title=\"Opennes Education Schedule\" href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/outline.htm\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>, </em>it will go from the <em>Open Definition</em> to the <em>Open Teaching</em>. Because I very motivated to learn about MOOC&#8217;s, specially <em>learning about teaching</em>, I decided to do one full course sMOOC (which is an Open Class), <em>Program for Online Teaching Certificate,Â </em>facilitate by <a title=\"Lisa M. Lane\" href=\"http://lisahistory.net/wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Lisa M. Lane</a>, <em><a title=\"PotCert\" href=\"http://pedagogyfirst.org/wppf12/\" target=\"_blank\">PotCert</a></em>, really very interesting, and also I want to do a complete open course. This is why I enrolled to the <em>Opennes in Education. #Potcert12</em> duration is a complete course in two semesters and <em>#oped12</em> is about twelve weeks. So I will combine this two courses during this first trimester.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">To be honest I am asking myself if I will have time enough to follow the courses because it takes time to read, see the videos, discuss, because it is not easy if you wanted to do it seriously and I really want to take profit.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">I decided to go seriously and to take part in both. I prepared a daily schedule with a <em>things to do listÂ </em>and I fixed a number of hours to dedicate to the courses. This is what I&#8217;ve done the last two weeks and it works very well.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">So, here I am today writing the first mail to share with you my motivation to do these courses.</p>\n<br /> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=filosofiadebolsillo.wordpress.com&#038;blog=28508677&#038;post=853&#038;subd=filosofiadebolsillo&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(354,8,0,'Africa must lead innovation in higher education internationalisation - University World News','Diigo','http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=20120912160836275',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/africa&quot;>africa</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/highered&quot;>highered</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/gsiemens&quot; title=&quot;View gsiemens &apos;s content in group&quot;>gsiemens </a></p>',1347895203,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mon, 17 Sep 2012 14:26:54 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(355,8,0,'What the Supreme Court&apos;s copyright rulings mean for you - Canada - CBC News','Diigo','http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2012/07/12/f-vp-nowak-copyright-ruling-consumer.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>A brief and readable overview of the Supreme Court&apos;s copyright rulings in July, 2012. - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/yukondude&quot; title=&quot;View Dave Rogers&apos;s content in group&quot;>Dave Rogers</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/fairdealing&quot;