 found or shared','14','<br /><strong>Connecting the Dots between Open Access and Open Educational Resources</strong>&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Another free SPARC online eventThursday, September 27th, 201212:00 - 1:00PM EDT (<a href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/meetingdetails.html?year=2012&amp;amp;month=9&amp;amp;day=27&amp;amp;hour=16&amp;amp;min=0&amp;amp;sec=0&amp;amp;p1=263\" style=\"color: #990099;\">use helpful time converter</a>)Registration is free, but required. Please&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://sparc.arl.org/civicrm/event/info?reset=1&amp;amp;id=110\" style=\"color: #990099;\">RSVP</a>&amp;nbsp;by September 25th.<br />This Webcast only requires an Internet connect (no phone dial in needed).<br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.arl.org/sparc/media/Webcast_OA_OER_Sept_27.shtml#.UFgL50NjEaM.blogger\">Webcast Invitation: Connecting the Dots between Open Access and Open Educational Resources September 27, 2012 (SPARC)</a><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7998294428961863698-1794426858296390345?l=notreallyalibrarian-markwashere.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(410,0,0,'something found or shared: #oped12 Why are Australian Universities avoiding t... http://t.co/LJ2Cfnad','twitter','http://twitter.com/Markfchris/statuses/248213812015149056',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/Markfchris/statuses/248213812015149056',NULL,NULL,29,'something found or shared: #<em>oped12</em> Why are Australian Universities avoiding t... <a href=\"http://t.co/LJ2Cfnad\">http://t.co/LJ2Cfnad</a>',1348014363,NULL,NULL,'Markfchris','http://twitter.com/Markfchris','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 00:15:59 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(411,24,0,'#oped12 Why are Australian Universities avoiding this movement?','text/html','http://notreallyalibrarian-markwashere.blogspot.com/2012/09/oped12-why-are-australian-universities.html','#oped12',NULL,NULL,21,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-19 10:14:54',37,'<a href=\"http://www.ocwconsortium.org/en/members/members\">Benefits of Membership</a> The mission of the <a href=\"http://www.ocwconsortium.org/\">OCW Consortium</a> is to serve both the individuals who use OCW and the institutions that make OCW possible. The Consortium provides a gateway to OCW projects and courses for the entire OCW community, fostering the success of the OCW movement and articulating its benefits. Through its public-relations efforts, the Consortium educates general audiences about the movement, directing potential users to resources that best suit their needs. For members, the Consortium marshals broad expertise regarding the ongoing development of open education projects and connects its members with an even broader network of OER practitioners. In other words, the OCW Consortium is an ideal meeting place for people wanting to make structured contributions to the development of open education worldwide.   <img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7998294428961863698-626342453038400008?l=notreallyalibrarian-markwashere.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1348017964,NULL,NULL,'markwashere','http://www.blogger.com/profile/16895029067006588081','2012-09-19T10:11:00.000+10:00',NULL,'something found or shared','15','<a href=\"http://www.ocwconsortium.org/en/members/members\">Benefits of Membership</a> The mission of the <a href=\"http://www.ocwconsortium.org/\">OCW Consortium</a> is to serve both the individuals who use OCW and the institutions that make OCW possible. The Consortium provides a gateway to OCW projects and courses for the entire OCW community, fostering the success of the OCW movement and articulating its benefits. Through its public-relations efforts, the Consortium educates general audiences about the movement, directing potential users to resources that best suit their needs. For members, the Consortium marshals broad expertise regarding the ongoing development of open education projects and connects its members with an even broader network of OER practitioners. In other words, the OCW Consortium is an ideal meeting place for people wanting to make structured contributions to the development of open education worldwide.   <img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7998294428961863698-626342453038400008?l=notreallyalibrarian-markwashere.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(412,3,0,'Gates foundation solicits remedial MOOCs | Inside Higher Ed','Diigo','http://www.insidehighered.com/news/2012/09/14/gates-foundation-solicits-remedial-moocs',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>Application for low-level courses - $5,000 - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/nagwanaga&quot; title=&quot;View Nagwa Abou El-Nga&apos;s content in group&quot;>Nagwa Abou El-Nga</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Highlights and Sticky Notes:</strong><p><DIV class=&quot;panel-pane pane-entity-field pane-node-field-article-smarttitle&quot; \njQuery1520039339349526911316=&quot;133&quot;>\n<DIV class=pane-content>\n<DIV \nclass=&quot;field field-name-field-article-smarttitle field-type-text field-label-hidden&quot;>\n<DIV class=field-items>\n<DIV class=&quot;field-item even&quot;>Gates, MOOCs and \nRemediation</DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV>\n<DIV class=panel-separator></DIV>\n<DIV class=&quot;panel-pane pane-node-created views-field views-field-created&quot; \njQuery1520039339349526911316=&quot;134&quot;>\n<DIV class=pane-content>September 14, 2012 - 3:00am </DIV></DIV>\n<DIV class=panel-separator></DIV>\n<DIV class=&quot;panel-pane pane-node-author&quot; jQuery1520039339349526911316=&quot;135&quot;>\n<H2 class=pane-title>By </H2>\n<DIV class=pane-content><A class=username title=&quot;View user profile.&quot; \nhref=&quot;http://www.insidehighered.com/users/paul-fain&quot;>Paul Fain</A> </DIV></DIV>\n<DIV class=panel-separator></DIV>\n<DIV class=&quot;panel-pane pane-entity-field pane-node-body&quot; \njQuery1520039339349526911316=&quot;136&quot;>\n<DIV class=pane-content>\n<DIV \nclass=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;>\n<DIV class=field-items>\n<DIV class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;>\n<P>Early returns show that massive open online courses (MOOCs) work best for \nmotivated and academically prepared students. But could high-quality MOOCs \nbenefit a broader range of learners, like those who get tripped up by remedial \nclasses?</P>\n<P>That&apos;s the question the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation <A \nhref=&quot;http://www.insidehighered.com/sites/default/server_files/files/MOOC%20RFP%20and%20Application.pdf&quot; \ntarget=_blank>wants to answer</A> with a newly announced round of 10 grants for \nthe creation of MOOCs for remedial coursework.</P>\n<P>\"We&apos;re trying to seed the conversation and seed the experimentation,\" said \nJosh Jarrett, the foundation&apos;s deputy director for education and postsecondary \neducation.</P>\n<P>MOOCs tend to provoke strong feelings in the academy, and in the wake of \nGates&apos;s announcement this week, some observers questioned whether free, widely \navailable online courses could be tailored to students with remedial needs. But \nothers, including experts on developmental learning, welcomed the attempt to \ntackle one of higher education&apos;s most vexing problems.</P>\n<P>\"This has the potential for raising the quality of instruction in \ndevelopmental education, if used properly,\" said Hunter R. Boylan, director of \nthe National Center for Developmental \nEducation.</P></DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV></p><p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/MOOC&quot;>MOOC</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/gates&quot;>gates</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/remediation&quot;>remediation</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/low-level&quot;>low-level</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/course&quot;>course</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/nagwanaga&quot; title=&quot;View Nagwa Abou El-Nga&apos;s content in group&quot;>Nagwa Abou El-Nga</a></p>',1348019283,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wed, 19 Sep 2012 00:47:19 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(413,0,0,'RT @gsiemens: finally, we have #oped12 newsletter, harvesting, aggregation working: http://t.co/4L4ejfSK . That was an ugly first week :(','twitter','http://twitter.com/Markfchris/statuses/248218401779109888',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/Markfchris/statuses/248218401779109888',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/gsiemens\">gsiemens</a>: finally, we have #<em>oped12</em> newsletter, harvesting, aggregation working: <a href=\"http://t.co/4L4ejfSK\">http://t.co/4L4ejfSK</a> . That was an ugly first week :(',1348019404,NULL,NULL,'Markfchris','http://twitter.com/Markfchris','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 00:34:13 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(414,5,0,'MOOC provide professional development','Diigo','http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/mooc-provide-professional-development-6459922',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>How do MOOC provide professional opportunities for emaployees? - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/nagwanaga&quot; title=&quot;View Nagwa Abou El-Nga&apos;s content in group&quot;>Nagwa Abou El-Nga</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/Professional&quot;>Professional</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/Development&quot;>Development</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/nagwanaga&quot; title=&quot;View Nagwa Abou El-Nga&apos;s content in group&quot;>Nagwa Abou El-Nga</a></p>',1348024323,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wed, 19 Sep 2012 02:14:48 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(415,0,0,'OTR Links 09/19/2012','text/html','http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/19/otr-links-09192012/','Links',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'Print from iOS with Dropbox, IFTTT and Automator &#124; 52 Tiger &#8220;The idea is to create a folder in Dropbox and attach a Folder Action to it that prints new additions. I use email to populate that folder and thereby &#8230; <a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/19/otr-links-09192012/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11046&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348035843,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 05:30:35 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<ul class=\"diigo-linkroll\">\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://52tiger.net/print-from-ios-dropbox-ifttt-automator/\">Print from iOS with Dropbox, IFTTT and Automator | 52 Tiger</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;The idea is to create a folder in Dropbox and attach a Folder Action to it that prints new additions. I use email to populate that folder and thereby trigger print jobs. Here&apos;s how to set it up with IFTTT, Dropbox and Apple&apos;s Automator.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/print\">print</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios\">ios</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/dropbox\">dropbox</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/automator\">automator</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/tiger\">tiger</a></p>\n<ul class=\"diigo-comments\">         </ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://edudemic.com/2012/09/report-vast-majority-of-top-u-s-schools-use-google-apps/\">Report: Vast Majority Of Top U.S. Schools Use Google Apps | Edudemic</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Google has just unveiled some new statistics on the uptake of its popular Google Apps In Education platform. Princeton has signed on which means 7 of the 8 Ivy League schools use Google Apps.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/report\">report</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google apps\">google apps</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/2012/09/18/watch-this-author-use-a-google-document-to-write-and-edit-a-book-in-real-time/\">Watch This Author Use A Google Document To Write And Edit A Book In Real-Time | TechCrunch</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;I can&apos;t imagine someone being able to watch every keystroke as I write a post like this, but author Silvia Hartmann is writing a novel, and is welcoming you to watch her progress. Live and in real-time.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/watch\">watch</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/author\">author</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/document\">document</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/book\">book</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/techcrunch\">techcrunch</a></p>\n<ul class=\"diigo-comments\">         </ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://mashable.com/2012/09/17/android-iphone-kid-safety/\">For Kids, Android Is Safer Than iOS</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;With the school year under way and the holiday season looming, a lot of kids are asking for (and getting) a new mobile device.</p>\n<p>Whatever sort of device you choose, it&apos;s important to turn on the appropriate parental controls. But before you decide on a gadget, you should be aware that some will be easier to control than others - and when it comes to parental controls, kids are much better off with an Android device rathern than an iPhone, iPad or iPod touch.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/kids\">kids</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/android\">android</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios\">ios</a></p>\n<ul class=\"diigo-comments\">         </ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://tweetbe.at/list-manager/\">TweetBe.at List Manager</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;TweetBe.at: The most powerful way to create and manage your Twitter lists.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/twitter\">twitter</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/lists\">lists</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://gadgetose.com/iphone-5-vs-iphone-4s-infographic/\">iPhone 5 vs iPhone 4S Infographic &#8211; GADGETOSE</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Here is a great infographic depicting the core differences between Apple&apos;s new iPhone 5 and its predecessor. Much faster than lurking Apple&apos;s site and comparing iPhone specifications back to back.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/iphone\">iphone</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/infographic\">infographic</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://elc60.prn.bc.ca/?p=394\">The Struggles of Educational Change | Energetic Learning Campus</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;I would consider the Energetic Learning Campus a catalyst of change for education but it has not been easy to convince our community. No matter how much I try to explain what we do, it always seems inadequate.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/change\">change</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/learning\">learning</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/campus\">campus</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"https://www.teachthought.com/social-media/25-tips-for-a-better-twitter-experience/\">25 Tips For A Better Twitter Experience | TeachThought</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Although LinkedIn gets a lot of love as a professional social media site, Twitter is a force (and a cognitively fertile stream as well) that can&apos;t be ignored by up-and-coming young professionals. It&apos;s a great place to get connected and informed, and an especially good resource for growing professionally. But how exactly can you use Twitter for professional development? Check out our list to find 25 different ways.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/tips\">tips</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/experience\">experience</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.thenerdyteacher.com/2012/09/what-is-instructional-technology.html\">The Nerdy Teacher: What is instructional technology?</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;My school is working to improve student achievement in many different ways. One way is having teachers join groups with a specific focus. The group I joined was for instructional technology. I feel like I know a thing or two about this topic and was excited to work with my staff.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/nerdy\">nerdy</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/teacher\">teacher</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/instructional\">instructional</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/instructional technology\">instructional technology</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/technology\">technology</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://edudemic.com/2012/09/why-a-colorado-k-12-school-now-resembles-an-internet-cafe/\">Why A Colorado K-12 School Now Resembles An Internet CafÃ© | Edudemic</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;After opening their new facility Sept. 12, Falcon Virtual Academy&apos;s faculty immediately started using its fresh mix of modern dÃ©cor and technology.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/colorado\">colorado</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/school\">school</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/internet\">internet</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/cafÃ©\">cafÃ©</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://designdisease.com/12-online-tools-apps-for-creating-amazing-websites/\">12 Online Tools &amp; Apps for Creating Amazing Websites | DesignDisease | Web and Graphic Design Blog</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Although learning to code and mastering desktop design applications are still very valuable skills, they&apos;re no longer a prerequisite for designing great websites.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/online\">online</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/online tools\">online tools</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/tools\">tools</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/apps\">apps</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/creating\">creating</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/websites\">websites</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/web\">web</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/graphic\">graphic</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/graphic design\">graphic design</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/design\">design</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/blog\">blog</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.digitaltrends.com/web/microsoft-warns-on-internet-explorer-security-flaw-urges-users-to-download-fix/\">IE security flaw: Microsoft urges users to install patch; experts suggest trying another browser | Digital Trends</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Following the discovery of a new security flaw in Internet Explorer, Microsoft is urging users to download a temporary fix. A number of security experts, meanwhile, suggest some may find it easier to temporarily switch to another browser instead.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/security\">security</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/microsoft\">microsoft</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/users\">users</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/patch\">patch</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/experts\">experts</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/browser\">browser</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/trends\">trends</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://anisesmithmarketing.com/2012/09/17/why-you-should-consider-learning-a-little-code-infographic/\">Why You Should Consider Learning A Little Code [Infographic] Â« Anise Smith Marketing</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Why You Should Consider Learning A Little CodeÂ [Infographic]&#8220;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/learning\">learning</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/little\">little</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/code\">code</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/infographic\">infographic</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/smith\">smith</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/marketing\">marketing</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://techli.com/2012/09/enemies-of-the-internet-infog/\">Enemies Of The Internet: Which Countries Have It The Worst (INFOGRAPHIC) | Techli</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Are we taking our open internet for granted? With the latest fights against cyber security bills like SOPA and CISPA, there&apos;s no doubt that internet censorship has become mainstream concern of the masses, particularly in the Western world. But do we really know just how bad some users around the world have it when they try to log on to the world wide web?&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/internet\">internet</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/countries\">countries</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/infographic\">infographic</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://churchm.ag/the-death-of-the-music-industry/\">The Death of the Music Industry? [Infographic] | ChurchMag</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;As much as we love the Internet, we can&apos;t deny it&apos;s huge impact on our lives and even on the economy. It has changed certain things for the better for sure. Even though I live in a small village, I can order anything I need via Amazon instead of having to drive 30 miles to a big city.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/death\">death</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/music\">music</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/industry\">industry</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/infographic\">infographic</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.greenbookblog.org/2012/09/17/data-visualization-the-new-art-of-understanding/\">Data Visualization &#8211; The New Art Of Understanding | GreenBook</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;As people begin to experiment with the creation and interpretation of visualizations and including them in presentations, a not-so-apparent shift will take place in the background where the traditional &apos;analyst&apos; role slowly morphs to give way to a new breed - the storytellers - who will be more strategic and consultative in nature and not data-waiters, statisticians or always comfortable with extreme analytics.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/data\">data</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/data visualization\">data visualization</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/visualization\">visualization</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/art\">art</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/understanding\">understanding</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.onlinedegrees.org/the-50-best-free-educational-apps-from-google-play/\">The 50 Best Free Educational Apps from Google Play &#8211; OnlineDegrees.org</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;The 50 Best Free Educational Apps from Google Play&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/free\">free</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/apps\">apps</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/play\">play</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/org\">org</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://thenextweb.com/google/2012/09/14/google-passes-500-chrome-experiments-continues-push-forward-latest-web-technologies/\">Google Passes 500 Chrome Experiments</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Google passes 500 Chrome Experiments, continues to push forward with the latest Web technologies&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/passes\">passes</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/chrome\">chrome</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/experiments\">experiments</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"diigo-ps\">Posted from <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com&apos;>Diigo</a>. The rest of my favorite links are <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete&apos;>here</a>.</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11046/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11046/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11046&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(416,0,0,'New View on Collaboration','text/html','https://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/19/new-view-on-collaboration/','application;Computers;Google;Teaching;collaboration;Google Doc;Google Document;Searching;Silvia Hartmann;Twitter;writing',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'&#160; So, yesterday, I read the article \"Watch This Author Use A Google Document To Write And Edit A Book In Real-Time\" and headed over to see what it was all about. Â It was very cool and lived up to &#8230; <a href=\"https://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/19/new-view-on-collaboration/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11043&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348045924,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 09:00:23 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>So, yesterday, I read the article \"<a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/2012/09/18/watch-this-author-use-a-google-document-to-write-and-edit-a-book-in-real-time/\">Watch This Author Use A Google Document To Write And Edit A Book In Real-Time</a>\" and headed over to see what it was all about. Â It was very cool and lived up to the expectations. Â Silvia Hartmann was writing a book titled \"The Dragon Lords\" and you could watch it happen on your screen.</p>\n<p>It was created in a Google Document <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AwxZlO1uVnFFKh_NWAlZ78oK2c5gxzvVCfrYbe7EOE8/preview?pli=1&amp;sle=true#heading=h.f0dths2bdy48\">here.</a></p>\n<p>Admittedly, this was really taking a chance but it was all there. Â Every time I went to it though, there were too many people online to get the full features but I got enough to get the idea.</p>\n<p>What an interesting concept! Â It makes you wonder about the wisdom of walled gardens. Â This would be an interesting activity for students but if they&apos;re locked behind a firewall requiring passwords/logins to their work, it just wouldn&apos;t happen.</p>\n<p>But imagine the opportunities for education!</p>\n<p>Imagine the following messages going out to one&apos;s PLN.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"I&apos;m writing a lesson plan on photosynthesis online here. Â If you are teaching the same thing or are an expert, please help me out.\"</li>\n<li>\"I have an essay due next week and I need some insights on horse training. Â Can anyone help me here?\"</li>\n<li>\"I&apos;m writing a blog post on a &apos;New View on Collaboration&apos; Â Want to throw in your two cents? Â Do so here.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our traditional view of sharing involves going to a repository and giving or taking. Â What if it involved co-creating with someone anywhere who might be more of an expert than you? Â What if you left a Google Document open to the world, with editing permissions, and asked for some help.</p>\n<p>What would happen?</p>\n<p>If you do make any changes, could you let me know where you&apos;re from? Â Twitter name too if so inclined.</p>\n<p>3:28 &#8211; 32 viewers<br />\n3:37 &#8211; 35 viewers<br />\n10:17 &#8211; 54 viewers</p>\n<hr />\n<p>I use Google Docs routinely in class. I let the students have their fun the first time they experience simultaneous collaboration (writing dirty words, deleting other students&apos; content, etc.), but after that it becomes a serious tool they never abuse (especially after I show them I can track all revisions!).</p>\n<p>I find that, even though they can view all other students&apos; work, they rarely edit or make suggestions on other students&apos; work, unless I specifically make it part of the assignment. Interestingly, they don&apos;t even ask others to review their work, even though they know it&apos;s super easy to do so.</p>\n<p>I have also used Google Docs to collaborate on province-wide writing projects. The ability to add comments specifically directed (and emailed) to certain authors (by pre-pending + to the email address of the author) makes it a very powerful and effective tool.</p>\n<p>Your idea about collaborating on a lesson plan is an excellent one, but it&apos;s something that I have never seen done outside of sponsored, paying writing jobs. I have my own theories about why that is, but those thoughts are best shared over an adult beverage, not in a public document.</p>\n<p>I believe Zoe has a public document that does not require a password to edit. Perhaps she can shed some light on her experience with that.</p>\n<p>@pbeens<br />\n<strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size:1em;\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul\">\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.thepowerbase.com/2012/09/author-silvia-hartmann-writing-novel-in-public-via-google-docs/\" target=\"_blank\">Author Silvia Hartmann Writing Novel in Public via Google Docs</a> (thepowerbase.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://reviews.cnet.com/8301-19512_7-20009065-233.html?part=rss&amp;subj=news&amp;tag=2547-1_3-0-20\" target=\"_blank\">Google Docs viewer on Android, iPhone, iPad browser? Why, yes</a> (reviews.cnet.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.gizmodo.co.uk/2012/09/watch-an-author-write-a-novel-live-on-google-docs/\" target=\"_blank\">Watch an Author Write a Novel Live on Google Docs</a> (gizmodo.co.uk)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/2012/09/18/watch-this-author-use-a-google-document-to-write-and-edit-a-book-in-real-time/\" target=\"_blank\">Watch This Author Use A Google Document To Write And Edit A Book In Real-Time</a> (techcrunch.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://publishingperspectives.com/2012/09/live-naked-writer-fantasy-author-invites-readers-to-watch-as-she-writes/\" target=\"_blank\">Live Naked Writer: Fantasy Author Invites Readers to Watch as She Writes</a> (publishingperspectives.com)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11043/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11043/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11043&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(417,0,0,'Patrick McAndrew, #OpenLearn talking about #OER #MOOC #REA at #aprendizajeenriquecido #Oped12','twitter','http://twitter.com/gema_bueno/statuses/248359801699069953',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/gema_bueno/statuses/248359801699069953',NULL,NULL,29,'Patrick McAndrew, <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23OpenLearn\" title=\"#OpenLearn\" class=\" \">#OpenLearn</a> talking about <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23OER\" title=\"#OER\" class=\" \">#OER</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23MOOC\" title=\"#MOOC\" class=\" \">#MOOC</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23REA\" title=\"#REA\" class=\" \">#REA</a> at <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23aprendizajeenriquecido\" title=\"#aprendizajeenriquecido\" class=\" \">#aprendizajeenriquecido</a> #<em>Oped12</em>',1348049642,NULL,NULL,'gema_bueno','http://twitter.com/gema_bueno','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 09:56:05 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(418,0,0,'corrected link for #oped12 reading Review of OER Movement: http://t.co/n4cPV9Xj original redirs to creative commons page which is also good!','twitter','http://twitter.com/benmsamuels/statuses/248345174944657408',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/benmsamuels/statuses/248345174944657408',NULL,NULL,29,'corrected link for #<em>oped12</em> reading Review of OER Movement: <a href=\"http://t.co/n4cPV9Xj\">http://t.co/n4cPV9Xj</a> original redirs to creative commons page which is also good!',1348049642,NULL,NULL,'benmsamuels','http://twitter.com/benmsamuels','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 08:57:58 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(419,6,0,'Can MOOC&apos;s Help Sell Textbooks? - Technology - The Chronicle of Higher Education','Diigo','http://chronicle.com/article/Can-MOOCs-Help-Sell/134446/',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>Colleges aren&apos;t the only enterprises interested in the possibilities of free, online courses. Publishers have begun to investigate whether so-called MOOC&apos;s, or massive open online courses, can help them reach new readers and sell more books. - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/rebeccahatherley&quot; title=&quot;View Rebecca Hatherley&apos;s content in group&quot;>Rebecca Hatherley</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Highlights and Sticky Notes:</strong><p>Publishers have begun to investigate whether so-called MOOC&apos;s, or massive open online courses, can help them reach new readers and sell more books.</p><p>But online courses do have recommended-reading lists, and enrollments in the tens of thousands. If even a small percentage of those online students buy books, the sales could add up to a nice boost for a textbook.</p><p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/textbooks&quot;>textbooks</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/education&quot;>education</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/MOOC&quot;>MOOC</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/OER&quot;>OER</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/openeducation&quot;>openeducation</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/publishing&quot;>publishing</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/motivation&quot;>motivation</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/oped12&quot;>oped12</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/MDDE622&quot;>MDDE622</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/copyright&quot;>copyright</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/rebeccahatherley&quot; title=&quot;View Rebecca Hatherley&apos;s content in group&quot;>Rebecca Hatherley</a></p>',1348054564,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wed, 19 Sep 2012 10:50:38 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(420,4,0,'What Do We Mean By &quot;Open&quot;?','Diigo','http://hackeducation.com/2012/09/18/define-open/',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>The adjective \"open\" ostensibly makes educational resources more easily accessible. But \"open\" can mean a lot of things: resources that are free; research that is publicly available on the Web and indexed by search engines; courses that offer open enrollment; materials that are openly licensed; content and code that can be copied and modified and redistributed. \"Open\" can mean \"transparent.\" Open versus proprietary. Open versus closed. - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/rebeccahatherley&quot; title=&quot;View Rebecca Hatherley&apos;s content in group&quot;>Rebecca Hatherley</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Highlights and Sticky Notes:</strong><p>I wonder about some of the recent MOOCs this way, for example. Sure, anyone can sign up so they&apos;re &quot;open&quot; in that sense. But the materials themselves often aren&apos;t openly licensed.</p><p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/education&quot;>education</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/open&quot;>open</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/OER&quot;>OER</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/openeducation&quot;>openeducation</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/MDDE622&quot;>MDDE622</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/oped12&quot;>oped12</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/rebeccahatherley&quot; title=&quot;View Rebecca Hatherley&apos;s content in group&quot;>Rebecca Hatherley</a></p>',1348054564,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wed, 19 Sep 2012 10:45:31 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(421,0,0,'xED Book  http://t.co/bxIIlO5n  Book about education stuff, moocs, et - in progress!  Siemens, Stewart, Cormier #oped12 #mooc','twitter','http://twitter.com/ifrank/statuses/248381193924526080',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/ifrank/statuses/248381193924526080',NULL,NULL,29,'xED Book <a href=\"http://t.co/bxIIlO5n\">http://t.co/bxIIlO5n</a> Book about education stuff, moocs, et - in progress! Siemens, Stewart, Cormier #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23mooc\" title=\"#mooc\" class=\" \">#mooc</a>',1348054683,NULL,NULL,'ifrank','http://twitter.com/ifrank','Wed, 19 Sep 2012 11:21:05 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(422,0,0,'RT @gema_bueno: Salvador Ros trying to define what are #MOOCs Maybe  #Oped12 http://t.co/wnXo8D7R is the answer http://t.co/M300hSbr  #a ...','twitter','http://twitter.com/varixto/statuses/248378521284657152',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/varixto/statuses/248378521284657152',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/gema_bueno\">gema_bueno</a>: Salvad