"diigo-linkroll\">\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://twitter.yfrog.com/h2s1ktp\">Doing some thinking about the constituent parts of web literacies: (more soon!)</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Doing some thinking about the constituent parts of web literacies: yfrog.com/h2s1ktp (more soon!)&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/doing\">doing</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/thinking\">thinking</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/parts\">parts</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/web\">web</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/literacies\">literacies</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://akipta.blogspot.ca/2012/09/girls-in-tech-world-endless.html?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+akipta+(A.+Kipta&apos;s+Blog)\">A. Kipta&#8217;s Blog: Girls in a Tech World: Endless Possibilities of Computer Science &#8211; YouTube</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">A. Kipta&#8217;s Blog: Girls in a Tech World: Endless Possibilities of Computer Science &#8211; YouTube</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/blog\">blog</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/girls\">girls</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/tech\">tech</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/world\">world</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/possibilities\">possibilities</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/computer\">computer</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/computer science\">computer science</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/science\">science</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/youtube\">youtube</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://techieminx.com/twitter-dm-phishing-scams-have-i-been-hacked.html\">Twitter DM Phishing Scams â€“ Have I been hacked ? | Techie Minx</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Twitter DM Phishing Scams â€“ Have I been hacked ?&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/phishing\">phishing</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/scams\">scams</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/hacked\">hacked</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/techie\">techie</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.sheknows.com/parenting/articles/816188/10-blogs-for-parents-of-kids-with-special-needs-1\">10 Blogs for special needs parents</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">Connecting with other parents is a great way to feel less alone and more connected. And if you&apos;re the parent of a child with special needs, the internet can be an amazing tool for finding other parents sharing your special journey. Here&#8217;s a roundup of some of the best blogs for special needs parents.</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/blogs\">blogs</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/special\">special</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/needs\">needs</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/parents\">parents</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://m.centerdigitaled.com/details/Why-Educators-Should-Spend-Time-Daily-on-Social-Media-165461476.html\">Why Educators Should Spend 15 Minutes a Day on Social Media</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Busy schedules are one reason why educators don&#8217;t collaborate and connect through social networking platforms. But a lack of time isn&#8217;t the main issue. It&#8217;s priorities.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/educators\">educators</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/minutes\">minutes</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/social\">social</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/social media\">social media</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/media\">media</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.joeyanne.co.uk/2012/09/17/five-free-methods-of-archiving-tweets-from-events-which-are-best/\">Joeyanne Libraryanne Â» Five free methods of archiving tweets from events â€“ which are best?</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;I&apos;ve been promising a number of people a blog post on how I archive tweets. I set archives up for lots of reasons â€“ often for an event I am attending to record tweets to refer to at a later date, or sometimes for projects I am involved in to keep a record of conversations. There are a number of different methods of archiving tweets, some of which are outlined below.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/twitter\">twitter</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/archive\">archive</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"diigo-ps\">Posted from <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com&apos;>Diigo</a>. The rest of my favorite links are <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete&apos;>here</a>.</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11055/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11055/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11055&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(446,0,0,'Mobile for ECOO 2012','text/html','http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/20/mobile-for-ecoo-2012/','Computers;ECOO;Education;learning;Facebook features;John Seely Brown;Keynote;Lanyrd;Michael Fullan;Nora Young;ontario;Teacher',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'&#160; Yesterday was a great planning day. Â Those of us on the ECOO 2012 Planning Committee got together to continue the process of making sure that everything is all set for this year&#8217;s conference on October 25, 26. Â The preconference &#8230; <a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/20/mobile-for-ecoo-2012/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11051&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348136643,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 09:00:00 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Yesterday was a great planning day. Â Those of us on the <a href=\"http://ecoo.org/\">ECOO 2012</a> Planning Committee got together to continue the process of making sure that everything is all set for this year&#8217;s conference on October 25, 26. Â The preconference on the 24th adds even more value to the conference attendees.</p>\n<p>As I <a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/07/\">blogged earlier</a>, the conference promises to be the most social ever &#8211; we&#8217;ve even got a Facebook page where we&#8217;re sharing some of the exciting sessions, one day at a time, highlighting the awesome sessions that will be offered by Ontario educators. Â The hashtag is in place &#8211; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/i//search/%23ECOO12\">#ECOO12</a> and folks are already discussing in anticipation.</p>\n<p>What would a good technology conference be without an app? Â We&#8217;ve got you covered there as well. Â We&#8217;re using the Lanyrd service to assemble and schedule all the component pieces. Â With an audience using such diverse technologies, it only makes sense to push the web application for those who like to plan ahead and explore everything!</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/2012-09-19-18-58-53.png?w=593\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>So, check it out on your mobile atÂ <a href=\"http://m.lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/\">http://m.lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/</a>Â or on your desktop atÂ <a href=\"http://lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/\">http://lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/</a>.</p>\n<p>Here you&#8217;ll be able to explore the event, plan your conference, see who&#8217;s attending, and read speaker biographies.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/2012-09-19-19-00-32.png?w=593\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>From top to bottom, there are great events with content designed to appeal to everyone. Â Nora Young is but one of the keynote speakers and she&#8217;s going to host a panel discussion of the other keynote speakers: Â <a href=\"http://lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/speakers/?q=Casap\">Jaime Casap</a>, <a href=\"http://lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/speakers/?q=Seely\">John Seely Brown</a>, and <a href=\"http://lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/speakers/?q=Fullan\">Michael Fullan</a>.</p>\n<p>The Committee is excited to see how all the pieces are starting to fall into place. Â Please take the time to bookmark the web application so that you can join in on the excitement and I hope to see you there.</p>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size:1em;\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul\">\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/12/2012-ecoo-conference/\" target=\"_blank\">2012 ECOO Conference</a> (dougpete.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/07/socially-gearing-up-for-the-ecoo-conference/\" target=\"_blank\">Socially Gearing up for the ECOO Conference</a> (dougpete.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/08/31/this-week-in-ontario-edublogs-30/\" target=\"_blank\">This Week in Ontario Edublogs</a> (dougpete.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/08/10/look-for-it/\" target=\"_blank\">Look for it</a> (dougpete.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/16/start-with-a-question-not-a-statement/\" target=\"_blank\">Start with a Question, not a Statement</a> (dougpete.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/14/an-interview-with-brenda-sherry-and-peter-skillen/\" target=\"_blank\">An Interview with Brenda Sherry and Peter Skillen</a> (dougpete.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://blog.programmableweb.com/2012/07/13/lanyrd-makes-foursquare-useful/\" target=\"_blank\">Lanyrd Makes Foursquare Useful</a> (programmableweb.com)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11051/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11051/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11051&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(447,7,0,'Live Stream Open Content Licensing Workshop - OpenCourseWare Europe','Diigo','http://opencourseware.eu/Workshop-Open-Content-licensing-in-Europe/live',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>Openness from this side of the Atlantic - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/opencourseware&quot;>opencourseware</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/europe&quot;>europe</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/openness&quot;>openness</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/OER&quot;>OER</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></p>',1348140243,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 20 Sep 2012 11:08:19 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(448,0,0,'RT @goldsmithsleu: Introduction to Openness in Education: An open online course led by David Wiley. http://t.co/1Ird50yA but not #oped12...','twitter','http://twitter.com/AnneHole/statuses/248743964159655937',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/AnneHole/statuses/248743964159655937',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/goldsmithsleu\">goldsmithsleu</a>: Introduction to Openness in Education: An open online course led by David Wiley. <a href=\"http://t.co/1Ird50yA\">http://t.co/1Ird50yA</a> but not #<em>oped12</em>...',1348140363,NULL,NULL,'AnneHole','http://twitter.com/AnneHole','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 11:22:37 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(449,0,0,'@yayin_ko I hope you enjoyed it though it was a bit simple and introductory. Let&apos;s read each !  #oped12','twitter','http://twitter.com/gema_bueno/statuses/248735863444496384',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/gema_bueno/statuses/248735863444496384',NULL,NULL,29,'@<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/yayin_ko\">yayin_ko</a> I hope you enjoyed it though it was a bit simple and introductory. Let&apos;s read each ! #<em>oped12</em>',1348140363,NULL,NULL,'gema_bueno','http://twitter.com/gema_bueno','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 10:50:25 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(450,0,0,'Why is neuroscience important in education? ','text/html','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/2012/09/why-is-neuroscience-important-in.html','brain',NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-20 14:59:55',19,'The following reasons are taken from the video below, which is a lecture on&amp;nbsp;the crossover between brain research and the classroom&amp;nbsp;by&amp;nbsp;Dr. Bryan Kolb from the Canadian Centre for Behavioural Science Research:<br /><h3>1. Debunking myths</h3><ol><li>10% myth â€“ we use ALL of it, you&apos;d know if you lost 5%</li><li>Left brain/right brain â€“ idea came from WWII veterans with bullet wounds, the two sides are doing different things, it&apos;s not as clear cut as the myth makes out</li><li>Brain development is done by age 3 â€“ our whole lives see brain development, including before we are even born</li><li>Girls and boys are the same - not...</li></ol><h3>2. Knowledge about brain development and function</h3>In the last decade, we&apos;ve learnt more about brain development than we could imagine would be known. And the implications of this for education are profound.<br /><h3>3. Informed solutions to practical issues:</h3><ol><li>Testing not only measures knowledge but also strengthens it</li><li>Exercise â€“ and play - enhances brain development and learning</li><li>Stress undermines learning and alters brain structure (&apos;bad&apos; stress - we do need some stress to stay alert)</li><li>Proper sleep cycles influence brain development and learning</li><li>Learning needs to be a serve and return strategy, not a passive process</li></ol><br /><object class=\"BLOGGER-youtube-video\" classid=\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" data-thumbnail-src=\"http://1.gvt0.com/vi/sxzdz4pobPk/0.jpg\" height=\"266\" width=\"320\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sxzdz4pobPk&amp;fs=1&amp;source=uds\" /><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" /><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" /><embed width=\"320\" height=\"266\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sxzdz4pobPk&amp;fs=1&amp;source=uds\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed></object><br /><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-7090770119026580364?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1348150083,NULL,NULL,'Bill Miller','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/','2012-09-20T14:48:00.001+01:00',NULL,'As Wonderful As Sunsets',NULL,'The following reasons are taken from the video below, which is a lecture on&amp;nbsp;the crossover between brain research and the classroom&amp;nbsp;by&amp;nbsp;Dr. Bryan Kolb from the Canadian Centre for Behavioural Science Research:<br /><h3>1. Debunking myths</h3><ol><li>10% myth â€“ we use ALL of it, you&apos;d know if you lost 5%</li><li>Left brain/right brain â€“ idea came from WWII veterans with bullet wounds, the two sides are doing different things, it&apos;s not as clear cut as the myth makes out</li><li>Brain development is done by age 3 â€“ our whole lives see brain development, including before we are even born</li><li>Girls and boys are the same - not...</li></ol><h3>2. Knowledge about brain development and function</h3>In the last decade, we&apos;ve learnt more about brain development than we could imagine would be known. And the implications of this for education are profound.<br /><h3>3. Informed solutions to practical issues:</h3><ol><li>Testing not only measures knowledge but also strengthens it</li><li>Exercise â€“ and play - enhances brain development and learning</li><li>Stress undermines learning and alters brain structure (&apos;bad&apos; stress - we do need some stress to stay alert)</li><li>Proper sleep cycles influence brain development and learning</li><li>Learning needs to be a serve and return strategy, not a passive process</li></ol><br /><object class=\"BLOGGER-youtube-video\" classid=\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" data-thumbnail-src=\"http://1.gvt0.com/vi/sxzdz4pobPk/0.jpg\" height=\"266\" width=\"320\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sxzdz4pobPk&amp;fs=1&amp;source=uds\" /><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" /><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" /><embed width=\"320\" height=\"266\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sxzdz4pobPk&amp;fs=1&amp;source=uds\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed></object><br /><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-7090770119026580364?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(451,0,0,'thx @jupidu I joined #oped12 and reading material from last week one: not surprisingly copyright + cc evolve - just like yesterday #ELT12','twitter','http://twitter.com/reimerth/statuses/248767188079624193',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/reimerth/statuses/248767188079624193',NULL,NULL,29,'thx @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/jupidu\">jupidu</a> I joined #<em>oped12</em> and reading material from last week one: not surprisingly copyright + cc evolve - just like yesterday <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23ELT12\" title=\"#ELT12\" class=\" \">#ELT12</a>',1348150443,NULL,NULL,'reimerth','http://twitter.com/reimerth','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 12:54:54 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(452,0,0,'Rory McGreal&apos;s blog','text/html','https://landing.athabascau.ca/bookmarks/view/66147/rory-mcgreals-blog',NULL,NULL,NULL,23,NULL,NULL,NULL,22,'<p>Rory is Athabasca University&apos;s&nbsp;Associate VP Research as well as being the&nbsp;UNESCO Chair in Open Educational Resources. His blog is full of interesting discussions and useful material relating to open access, copyright, patent law and so on, generally with an emphasis on how such things relate to education.</p><p>Address of the bookmark: <a href=\"https://landing.athabascau.ca/pg/blog/owner/rory\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://landing.athabascau.ca/pg/blog/owner/rory</a></p>',1348152491,NULL,NULL,'Rory McGreal','https://landing.athabascau.ca/blog/owner/rory','Tue, 26 Apr 2011 12:48:29 -0600',NULL,'CDATA(0)',NULL,'<p>Rory is Athabasca University&apos;s&nbsp;Associate VP Research as well as being the&nbsp;UNESCO Chair in Open Educational Resources. His blog is full of interesting discussions and useful material relating to open access, copyright, patent law and so on, generally with an emphasis on how such things relate to education.</p><p>Address of the bookmark: <a href=\"https://landing.athabascau.ca/pg/blog/owner/rory\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://landing.athabascau.ca/pg/blog/owner/rory</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(453,0,0,'OER: A business case?','text/html','https://landing.athabascau.ca/blog/view/165341/oer-a-business-case',NULL,NULL,NULL,23,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,'<p>The following resources sent by Cable Grreen of Creative Commons might be useful:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.col.org/resources/publications/Pages/detail.aspx?PID=421\">http://www.col.org/resources/publications/Pages/detail.aspx?PID=421</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://thepowerofopen.org/\">http://thepowerofopen.org/</a> <br><br></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://edtechfrontier.com/2012/03/04/the-economics-of-open/\">http://edtechfrontier.com/2012/03/04/the-economics-of-open/</a></li>\n<li>Business case for OER:</li>\n<li>increase access to education</li>\n<li>provide students with an opportunity to assess and plan their education choices</li>\n<li>showcase an institution&rsquo;s intellectual outputs, promote it&rsquo;s profile, and attract students</li>\n<li>convert students exploring options into fee paying enrollments</li>\n<li>accelerate learning by providing educational resources for just-in-time, direct, informal use by both students and self-directed learners</li>\n<li>add value to knowledge production</li>\n<li>reduce faculty preparation time</li>\n<li>generate cost savings &ndash; (this case has been particularly substantiated for open textbooks)</li>\n<li>enhance quality</li>\n<li>generate innovation through collaboration</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cable</p>\n',1348154288,NULL,NULL,'Rory McGreal','https://landing.athabascau.ca/blog/owner/rory','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 08:53:36 -0600',NULL,'CDATA(0)',NULL,'<p>The following resources sent by Cable Grreen of Creative Commons might be useful:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.col.org/resources/publications/Pages/detail.aspx?PID=421\">http://www.col.org/resources/publications/Pages/detail.aspx?PID=421</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://thepowerofopen.org/\">http://thepowerofopen.org/</a> <br><br></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://edtechfrontier.com/2012/03/04/the-economics-of-open/\">http://edtechfrontier.com/2012/03/04/the-economics-of-open/</a></li>\n<li>Business case for OER:</li>\n<li>increase access to education</li>\n<li>provide students with an opportunity to assess and plan their education choices</li>\n<li>showcase an institution&rsquo;s intellectual outputs, promote it&rsquo;s profile, and attract students</li>\n<li>convert students exploring options into fee paying enrollments</li>\n<li>accelerate learning by providing educational resources for just-in-time, direct, informal use by both students and self-directed learners</li>\n<li>add value to knowledge production</li>\n<li>reduce faculty preparation time</li>\n<li>generate cost savings &ndash; (this case has been particularly substantiated for open textbooks)</li>\n<li>enhance quality</li>\n<li>generate innovation through collaboration</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cable</p>\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(454,21,0,'Openness in Education Mooc #oped12','text/html','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/2012/09/openness-in-education-mooc-oped12.html','#oped12',NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-20 16:28:10',19,'Although deluged with other things, I&apos;m really happy to be registered for this, my second Mooc (my first was <a href=\"http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.co.uk/2012/07/11-days-in-july-google-power-searching.html\">Power Searching with Google</a>). I&apos;ve done my best to catch up with the reading although I haven&apos;t engaged with fellow Moocers yet - I will rectify this...<br /><br />In week 1 I read <a href=\"http://www.oecd.org/edu/ceri/38654317.pdf\">Giving Knowledge for Free: the emergence of open educational resources</a>, which offers a good overview of Open Educational Resources and the impact (or not) on higher education. It&apos;s a great place to start - especially as brain research tells us that we prefer the big picture view before trying to fit it all together...<br /><br />The best for me this week has been a fascinating <a href=\"http://www.mcs.open.ac.uk/80256EE9006B7FB0/(httpAssets)/F4D49088F191D0BF80256F870042AB9D/$file/History+of+the+Open+University.pdf\">History of the Open University</a> - I knew Harold Wilson figured large in this but had never heard of Jennie Lee, without whom, it seems, the whole project would have failed...<br /><br />And I&apos;ve also got round at least to having a look at the Twitter stream for the course - and just wow, it really is interesting - just have a look at this beautiful set of notes for Week 1 reading <a href=\"http://firstmonday.org/htbin/cgiwrap/bin/ojs/index.php/fm/article/view/1472/1387\">The Cathedral and the Bazaar</a> from @giuliaforsythe:<br /><a href=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8302/7985992388_fdd260009c_o.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8302/7985992388_fdd260009c_o.jpg\" width=\"320\" /></a><br />Amazing! Anyway, here&apos;s the main course portal:&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/index.html\">http://open.mooc.ca/index.html</a>&amp;nbsp;and the hashtag is #oped12 if you want to have a look and see what people are saying on Twitter.<img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-9062503221108607133?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1348155123,NULL,NULL,'Bill Miller','http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com/','2012-09-20T16:28:00.000+01:00',NULL,'As Wonderful As Sunsets','9','Although deluged with other things, I&apos;m really happy to be registered for this, my second Mooc (my first was <a href=\"http://aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.co.uk/2012/07/11-days-in-july-google-power-searching.html\">Power Searching with Google</a>). I&apos;ve done my best to catch up with the reading although I haven&apos;t engaged with fellow Moocers yet - I will rectify this...<br /><br />In week 1 I read <a href=\"http://www.oecd.org/edu/ceri/38654317.pdf\">Giving Knowledge for Free: the emergence of open educational resources</a>, which offers a good overview of Open Educational Resources and the impact (or not) on higher education. It&apos;s a great place to start - especially as brain research tells us that we prefer the big picture view before trying to fit it all together...<br /><br />The best for me this week has been a fascinating <a href=\"http://www.mcs.open.ac.uk/80256EE9006B7FB0/(httpAssets)/F4D49088F191D0BF80256F870042AB9D/$file/History+of+the+Open+University.pdf\">History of the Open University</a> - I knew Harold Wilson figured large in this but had never heard of Jennie Lee, without whom, it seems, the whole project would have failed...<br /><br />And I&apos;ve also got round at least to having a look at the Twitter stream for the course - and just wow, it really is interesting - just have a look at this beautiful set of notes for Week 1 reading <a href=\"http://firstmonday.org/htbin/cgiwrap/bin/ojs/index.php/fm/article/view/1472/1387\">The Cathedral and the Bazaar</a> from @giuliaforsythe:<br /><a href=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8302/7985992388_fdd260009c_o.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"240\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8302/7985992388_fdd260009c_o.jpg\" width=\"320\" /></a><br />Amazing! Anyway, here&apos;s the main course portal:&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/index.html\">http://open.mooc.ca/index.html</a>&amp;nbsp;and the hashtag is #oped12 if you want to have a look and see what people are saying on Twitter.<img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/3680182410838117036-9062503221108607133?l=aswonderfulassunsets.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(455,0,0,'RT @giuliaforsythe: The Cathedral &amp;amp; The Bazaar OPENBLOCKvisual notesCLOSEBLOCK #oped12 http://t.co/T8l4y10V','twitter','http://twitter.com/learnwonder/statuses/248805992983318529',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/learnwonder/statuses/248805992983318529',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/giuliaforsythe\">giuliaforsythe</a>: The Cathedral &amp;amp; The Bazaar OPENBLOCKvisual notesCLOSEBLOCK #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://t.co/T8l4y10V\">http://t.co/T8l4y10V</a>',1348155483,NULL,NULL,'learnwonder','http://twitter.com/learnwonder','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 15:29:05 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(456,0,0,'la scuola e il digitale sbagliato','text/html','http://serenaturri.wordpress.com/2012/09/20/2169/','Uncategorized',NULL,NULL,20,NULL,NULL,NULL,36,'Reblogged from salvo esaurimento scorte: Mio figlio inizia la scuola media, vado alla sede scolastica e prendo la lista dei libri. Sono tanti, quattordici. A occhio e croce devo spendere poco meno di trecento euro. Mi dico, beh una circolare del Ministero dell&#8217;Istruzione dice che dal 2012/2013 i testi devono essere presenti anche in digitale. [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=serenaturri.wordpress.com&#038;blog=9618855&#038;post=2169&#038;subd=serenaturri&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348158964,NULL,NULL,'serenaturri','http://serenaturri.wordpress.com','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 16:16:35 +0000',NULL,'serenaturri&#039;s Blog',NULL,'<p class=\"reblog-from\"><img alt=&apos;&apos; src=&apos;http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/231857e6b2ae1ae69580139123cf30e2?s=25&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G&apos; class=&apos;avatar avatar-25&apos; height=&apos;25&apos; width=&apos;25&apos; /> <a href=\"http://salvoesaurimentoscorte.wordpress.com/2012/09/14/la-scuola-e-il-digitale-sbagliato/\">Reblogged from salvo esaurimento scorte:</a></p>\n<p>Mio figlio inizia la scuola media, vado alla sede scolastica e prendo la lista dei libri. Sono tanti, quattordici. A occhio e croce devo spendere poco meno di trecento euro.\nMi dico, beh una circolare del Ministero dell&#8217;Istruzione dice che dal 2012/2013 i testi devono essere presenti anche in digitale. ChissÃ  che non sia piÃ¹ conveniente comprarli in digitale e fornire al primogenito un tablet o un ebook reader.</p>\n <p class=\"read-more\"><a href=\"http://salvoesaurimentoscorte.wordpress.com/2012/09/14/la-scuola-e-il-digitale-sbagliato/\" target=\"_self\">Continua a leggere... 658 more words</a></p> ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(457,0,0,'@WendyDrexler has inspired my Instructional Design for the Open Classroom  See how: http://t.co/lIz2SL0W  #oped12 #vsmooc12','twitter','http://twitter.com/verenanz/statuses/248828640815640576',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/verenanz/statuses/248828640815640576',NULL,NULL,29,'@<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/WendyDrexler\">WendyDrexler</a> has inspired my Instructional Design for the Open Classroom See how: <a href=\"http://t.co/lIz2SL0W\">http://t.co/lIz2SL0W</a> #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23vsmooc12\" title=\"#vsmooc12\" class=\" \">#vsmooc12</a>',1348160523,NULL,NULL,'verenanz','http://twitter.com/verenanz','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 16:59:05 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(458,0,0,'Paperless school in Italy is very far away in the future. http://t.co/tEkxFb0Y  #oped12 All closed digital formats to protect publishers.','twitter','http://twitter.com/JaapSoft/statuses/248824806278041601',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/JaapSoft/statuses/248824806278041601',NULL,NULL,29,'Paperless school in Italy is very far away in the future. <a href=\"http://t.co/tEkxFb0Y\">http://t.co/tEkxFb0Y</a> #<em>oped12</em> All closed digital formats to protect publishers.',1348160523,NULL,NULL,'JaapSoft','http://twitter.com/JaapSoft','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 16:43:51 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(459,0,0,'Openness in Education Mooc #oped12: Although deluged with other things, I&apos;m really happy to be registered for th... http://t.co/BidMPXCo','twitter','http://twitter.com/learnwonder/statuses/248816977148256256',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/learnwonder/statuses/248816977148256256',NULL,NULL,29,'Openness in Education Mooc #<em>oped12</em>: Although deluged with other things, I&apos;m really happy to be registered for th... <a href=\"http://t.co/BidMPXCo\">http://t.co/BidMPXCo</a>',1348160523,NULL,NULL,'learnwonder','http://twitter.com/learnwonder','Thu, 20 Sep 2012 16:12:44 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(460,24,0,'Wendy Drexler &#8211; Creation of PLE in Grade 7 science class  #oped12 #vsmooc12','text/html','http://www.openclassroomonline.com/wendy-drexler-creation-of-ple-in-grade-7-science-class/','Uncategorized',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,24,'I think that Wendy Drexler&#8217;s research on the creation of PLE&#8217;s in the science classroom is the very close to what I am thinking in the creation of the Open Classroom &#8211; courses. Although the courses will be much shorter, &#8230; <a href=\"http://www.openclassroomonline.com/wendy-drexler-creation-of-ple-in-grade-7-science-class/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a>',1348162807,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 20 Sep 2012 16:46:56 +0000',NULL,'Creating an Open Classroom','14','<p>I think that Wendy Drexler&#8217;s research on the creation of PLE&#8217;s in the science classroom is the very close to what I am thinking in the creation of the Open Classroom &#8211; courses. Although the courses will be much shorter, but ultimately lead to a project, Wendy&#8217;s student completed their Open Course -in their regular f2f classroom.</p>\n<p>Wendy&#8217;s Research: <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/file/d/0BwgtH7cIrVEwZmFiYjEzZjItYWQ2YS00NzlmLWI3Y2YtY2EwOGI5MjJmMDBj/edit?hl=en\">A Networked Learning Model for Construction of a Personal Learning Environment</a></p>\n<p>This is the outline of the unit forÂ Science 7:</p>\n<p><em><strong>The Networked Student Unit Plan â€“ 9 Weeks</strong></em><br />\n<strong>Unit Objective:</strong> The student will model the scientific method through the construction of<br />\npersonal learning environments to research a self-selected topic in life science.</p>\n<p><strong>Preparation â€“ 2 weeks</strong><br />\nâ€¢ Teacher introduces the scientific method, what it means to be a scientist, and how to<br />\nthink like a scientist. Students embark on a scientific exploration based on the scientific<br />\nmethod. Each student selects his or her topic of study, conducts a KWL (what you<br />\nknow, what you want to know, what you learn), and establishes a research question and<br />\nhypothesis.<br />\nâ€¢ Acceptable/Responsible Use Policy is discussed and signed by each participating<br />\nstudent.<br />\nâ€¢ The project is positioned within the following perspective. What if your teachers<br />\ndisappeared and you had to learn on your own? Would you give up on learning? Where<br />\nwould you begin? Why would learning be important? You are an empowered learner.<br />\nYou have the power to learn anything. How much you learn is up to you. How you<br />\nmanage your learning is up to you. How you manage your time is up to you. A big part<br />\nof your success will depend on how well you are organized.</p>\n<table width=\"834\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><big><strong>Introduction of Tools â€“ 2 weeks</strong></big>Web applications are introduced one at a time to give<br />\nstudents the chance to master the toolÂ within the context of the study topic. Digital literacy isÂ integrated into these lessons as needed.Â The essential questions of digital literacy are presented.Â Where can you go for goodÂ information? How do you know if you can trust what you find?Â How will you find subjectÂ matter experts you can trust to help you learn? Why isÂ reflection important when you areÂ learning something new? Why is it important to share whatÂ you&apos;ve learned? How will youÂ share?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Web Application </strong>(Networked<br />\nStudentComponent)</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Tool Used in<br />\nPrototype</strong></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Student Activity</strong><strong></strong><strong>Level of Structure</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Social Bookmarking (RSS)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Delicious<a href=\"http://delicious.com/\">http://delicious.com/</a></td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Explain Really Simple</li>\n<li>Syndication (RSS) and evaluation of Websites</li>\n<li>Set up the account</li>\n<li>Subscribe to each others</li>\n<li>accounts</li>\n<li>Bookmark and read at least 5 reliable websites<br />\nthat reflect the</li>\n<li>content of chosen topic</li>\n<li>Add and read at least 3 additional sites each<br />\nweek.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Note Taking (InformationManagement)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">NoteFish<a href=\"http://www.notefish.com\">http://www.notefish.co</a>m</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Create NoteFish account</li>\n<li>Begin content collection</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">News and Blog Alert (RSS)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Google Alert<a href=\"http://www.google.com/alerts\">http://www.google.com/</a>alerts</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Create a Google Alert of keywords associated<br />\nwith selected topic</li>\n<li>Read news and blogs on that topic that are<br />\ndelivered via email daily</li>\n<li>Subscribe to appropriate blogs in reader</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Personal Web Aggregator(RSS, InformationManagement)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Symbaloo<a href=\"http://symbaloo.com\">http://symbaloo.com</a></td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Introduce Symbaloo</li>\n<li>Customize page</li>\n<li>Start by creating a social bookmarking gadget</li>\n<li>This will build as students learn new tools</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">News and Blog Reader(RSS)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Symbaloo RSS Feeds<a href=\"http://symbaloo.com\">http://symbaloo.com</a></td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Search for blogs and newsfeeds devoted to<br />\nchosen topic</li>\n<li>Subscribe to blogs and newsfeeds to keep track<br />\nof updates.</li>\n<li>Set up gadgets in Symbaloo</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Personal Blog (RSS)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">EduBlogs<a href=\"http://www.edublogs.org\">http://www.edublogs.or</a>g</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Create a personal blog</li>\n<li>Post a personal reflection each day of the<br />\ncontent found and experiences related to the use<br />\nof personal learning environment</li>\n<li>Students with similar topics subscribe to each<br />\nothers blogs in reader</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Internet Search(Information Management,Contacts, and SynchronousCommunication)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Google Scholar<a href=\"http://scholar.google.com/\">http://scholar.google.co</a>m/</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Conduct searches in Google</li>\n<li>Scholar and library databases for scholarly<br />\nworks.</li>\n<li>Bookmark appropriate sites</li>\n<li>Consider making contact with expert for video<br />\nconference</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Podcasts (RSS)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">TunesU<a href=\"http://www.apple.com/itunes/whatson/itunesu.html\">http://www.apple.com/it</a>unes/whatson/itunesu.html</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Search iTunesU for podcasts related to topic</li>\n<li>Listen to at least 2 podcasts if possible</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Video Conferencing (Contacts and<br />\nSynchronousCommunication)</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Skypehttp://www.skype.com</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Identify at least one subject matter expert to<br />\ninvite to Skype with the class.</li>\n<li>Video Conferencing</li>\n<li>(Contacts and Synchronous Communication)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Daily research, reflection, share 3 weeks</strong></p>\n<p>Once the personal learning environment is constructed, theÂ student will continue to conductÂ research and navigate new content on a daily basis. DailyÂ activities should be dividedÂ between introducing a tip or offering a research theme forÂ the day, actual time spentÂ conducting research, ten minutes to reflect, and 15 minutesÂ to share</p>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Content Synthesis 1-2 Weeks</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Glogster<a href=\"http://www.glogster.com\">http://www.glogster.com<br />\n</a></td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Digital science poster in glogster to reflect<br />\nstudent research within the context the<br />\nscientific method</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This is a student video based on the project:<br />\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/YEls3tq5wIY\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Now I need to think about how I can apply #oc courses into an open environment. At least I have a fantastic template.</p>\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(461,2,0,'EIF main conference | EFQUEL Innovation Forum','Diigo','http://eif.efquel.org/programme/conference-days/',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/no_tag&quot;>no_tag</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></p>',1348165443,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 20 Sep 2012 18:22:07 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(462,4,0,'National Symposium on Open Education - WikiEducator','Diigo','http://wikieducator.org/Otago_Polytechnic/National_Symposium_on_Open_Education',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>From the Antipodes - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/no_tag&quot;>no_tag</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></p>',1348165443,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 20 Sep 2012 18:21:03 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(463,6,0,'Google Launches Free Tool To Let You Run Your Own Online Courses | Edudemic','Diigo','http://edudemic.com/2012/09/google-course-builder/',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/no_tag&quot;>no_tag</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></p>',1348165443,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 20 Sep 2012 18:19:03 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(464,5,0,'Nov 13 MOOCs: An Evolving Model of Curriculum Delivery and Assessment Â« Community College Consortium for Open Educational Resources','Diigo','http://oerconsortium.org/nov-13-moocs-an-evolving-model-of-curriculum-delivery-and-assessment