> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23TLTGmooc1\" title=\"#TLTGmooc1\" class=\" \">#TLTGmooc1</a>',1348266483,NULL,NULL,'ifrank','http://twitter.com/ifrank','Fri, 21 Sep 2012 21:46:12 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(498,0,0,'Reshared post from Esther Wojcicki:','text/html','https://plus.google.com/110117137800261731479/posts/comFNbm7K3M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,'Many people assume that MOOCs will leave professors out of jobs. I really don&#39;t think so. I think that, ten years from now, there will be many jobs for professors who can harness the power of the Internet.Quote:Â &quot;What the Internet has proven with resounding success is that it can connect writers with real audiences&quot;<hr/><p><strong><a href=&apos;https://plus.google.com/102774783758711593873/posts/XvvGGWCYUjD&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Original Post</a> from <a href=&apos;https://plus.google.com/102774783758711593873&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Esther Wojcicki</a>:</strong></p><p>Interesting discussion about the value of MOOCs like Coursera</p><p class=&apos;attachment article&apos;>\n										<a href=&apos;http://dmlcentral.net/blog/john-jones/online-learning-and-teaching-writing&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Online Learning and Teaching Writing | DMLcentral</a>\n									</p><p class=&apos;attachment photo&apos;>\n										<a href=&apos;http://dmlcentral.net/blog/john-jones/online-learning-and-teaching-writing&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;><img src=&apos;https://images0-focus-opensocial.googleusercontent.com/gadgets/proxy?container=focus&gadget=a&resize_h=100&url=http%3A%2F%2Fdmlcentral.net%2Fsites%2Fdmlcentral%2Ffiles%2Fimagecache%2Fblog_image%2Fblog_images%2Fjohnjones.30.600.jpg&apos; height=&apos;100&apos;/> </a>\n									</p>',1348272004,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fri, 21 Sep 2012 23:55:47 +0200',NULL,'CDATA(0)',NULL,'Many people assume that MOOCs will leave professors out of jobs. I really don&#39;t think so. I think that, ten years from now, there will be many jobs for professors who can harness the power of the Internet.Quote:Â &quot;What the Internet has proven with resounding success is that it can connect writers with real audiences&quot;<hr/><p><strong><a href=&apos;https://plus.google.com/102774783758711593873/posts/XvvGGWCYUjD&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Original Post</a> from <a href=&apos;https://plus.google.com/102774783758711593873&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Esther Wojcicki</a>:</strong></p><p>Interesting discussion about the value of MOOCs like Coursera</p><p class=&apos;attachment article&apos;>\n										<a href=&apos;http://dmlcentral.net/blog/john-jones/online-learning-and-teaching-writing&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Online Learning and Teaching Writing | DMLcentral</a>\n									</p><p class=&apos;attachment photo&apos;>\n										<a href=&apos;http://dmlcentral.net/blog/john-jones/online-learning-and-teaching-writing&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;><img src=&apos;https://images0-focus-opensocial.googleusercontent.com/gadgets/proxy?container=focus&gadget=a&resize_h=100&url=http%3A%2F%2Fdmlcentral.net%2Fsites%2Fdmlcentral%2Ffiles%2Fimagecache%2Fblog_image%2Fblog_images%2Fjohnjones.30.600.jpg&apos; height=&apos;100&apos;/> </a>\n									</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(499,0,0,'OTR Links 09/22/2012','text/html','http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/22/otr-links-09222012/','Links',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'Harvard Referencing Generator &#124; Essay Tool Box &#8220;Once generated you can simply copy and paste it in to your work. Now you&#8217;ll never need to worry about malformed Harvard references again!&#8221; tags: referencing research harvard reference Bibliography citation generator citations &#8230; <a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/22/otr-links-09222012/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11078&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348293243,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 05:30:33 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<ul class=\"diigo-linkroll\">\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.ukessays.com/tool-box/harvard-referencing-generator/\">Harvard Referencing Generator | Essay Tool Box</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Once generated you can simply copy and paste it in to your work. Now you&#8217;ll never need to worry about malformed Harvard references again!&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/referencing\">referencing</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/research\">research</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/harvard\">harvard</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/reference\">reference</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/Bibliography\">Bibliography</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/citation\">citation</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/generator\">generator</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/citations\">citations</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://paulbourke.net/fractals/googleearth/\">Google Earth Fractals</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;The following is a &#8220;photographic&#8221; gallery of fractals patterns found while exploring the planet with Google Earth. Each is provided with a KMZ file so the reader can explore the region for themselves. Readers are encouraged to submit their own KMZ files for inclusion, credits will be included.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/fractals\">fractals</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/photography\">photography</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/geography\">geography</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/earth\">earth</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/googleearth\">googleearth</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.livebinders.com/play/play?id=26265\">Google Docs &#8211; LiveBinder</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Google Docs&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/docs\">docs</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/livebinder\">livebinder</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google docs\">google docs</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.educatorstechnology.com/2012/09/writing-rules-for-teachers.html\">9 Golden Rules for Good Writing</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Writing is an art which, fortunately, can be learned and not acquired. Everybody of us has the potential of being a writer but Â only some succeed in being so. Some are occasional writers, others become writers only in the day of exam, but there is another category who write for a living. Whatever your purpose behind writing, knowing how to master this art is a Â must for the 21st century literates.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/rules\">rules</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/writing\">writing</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://1hundredzeros.blogspot.ca/2011/07/why-google-cloud-is-secure-for.html\">100 Zeros: Why The Google Cloud Is Secure For Education</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Google Plus looks like it already hit 20 million users in under a month and the chatter about it coming to Google Apps is loud. Â I have heard the security conversation catching up in volume as we revisit whether cloud computing can offer the security we want for our students and schools. Knowledge is power so if you still are learning about Google Plus see Steve Anderson&#8217;s collection of Google Plus goodies. If you are ready for the security truth then here it is: Google&#8217;s cloud storage is more secure than anything you are doing.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/cloud\">cloud</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/education\">education</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.polleverywhere.com/ars-comparison\">Audience Response System Comparison | Poll Everywhere</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;When we first tried to learn about Audience Response Systems, it quickly became overwhelming. First, they go by many names: Classroom clickers, voting keypads, classroom performance systems, classroom response systems, personal response systems, student response systems, audience polling, interactive meetings&#8230; Wow. Yikes!&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ARS\">ARS</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/Voting\">Voting</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/inspiration\">inspiration</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/systems\">systems</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/poll\">poll</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/rocktober\">rocktober</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ideas\">ideas</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"https://www.pcworld.com/article/2009768/web-browser-showdown-which-windows-app-is-really-the-best.html\">Web browser showdown: Which Windows app is really the best? | PCWorld</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;We put the three major Windows browsers-Google Chrome 21, Microsoft Internet Explorer 9, and Mozilla Firefox 15-through their paces and crowned an overall winner.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/web\">web</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/browser\">browser</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/windows\">windows</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/windows app\">windows app</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/app\">app</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/pcworld\">pcworld</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://thenextweb.com/apps/2012/09/21/twitter-ios-6-iphone/?awesm=tnw.to_i5AB\">Twitter for iOS is Now Optimized for the iPhone 5 and iOS 6</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Twitter for iOS is now optimized for the iPhone 5 and iOS 6&#8243;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios\">ios</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/optimized\">optimized</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/iphone\">iphone</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.nirmaltv.com/2012/09/21/how-to-post-to-twitter-and-facebook-from-ios-6-notification-area/\">How to Post to Twitter and Facebook from iOS 6 Notification Area</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;One of the improvements in iOS 6 is the social sharing options. Earlier with iOS 5, Twitter was integrated with iOS and now with the release of iOS6, Apple has added Facebook integration. We have already covered on how to set up Facebook integration in iOS6. Another good feature with respect to Twitter and Facebook integration is that you can quickly Tweet or share a post to Facebook from the notification in iOS 6.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/how to\">how to</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/post\">post</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/facebook\">facebook</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios\">ios</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/notification\">notification</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/area\">area</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.joebower.org/2010/11/something-we-create-for-ourselves.html?m=1\">for the love of learning: Something we create for ourselves</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Technology has not only revolutionized how the masses share information, but it has also liberated the masses to be creators of information. No longer do the select,Â privilegedÂ few maintain a monopoly on content.Â &#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/learning\">learning</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/something\">something</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ourselves\">ourselves</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.lockergnome.com/ios/2012/09/20/mapsgate-is-not-the-end-of-the-road/\">Mapsgate is Not the End of the Road &#8211; LockerGnome</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;So, the new default Maps app in the first release of iOS 6 is a dud according to most of the world - so who am I to argue?&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/road\">road</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/maps\">maps</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios6\">ios6</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://sachagreif.com/why-programming-languages-sites-are-ugly/\">Why Are Programming Languages Sites So Ugly? | SachaGreif.com</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;For some reason I&apos;ve been spending a lot of time on Hacker News lately. And I couldn&apos;t help but notice that the Go language is getting a lot of hype.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/programming\">programming</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/languages\">languages</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/sites\">sites</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/com\">com</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"https://allthingsd.com/20120920/the-fine-print-on-twitters-latest-developer-dust-up-with-ifttt/\">The Fine Print on Twitter&#8217;s Latest Developer Dustup With IFTTT &#8211; Mike Isaac &#8211; Social &#8211; AllThingsD</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Despite being constantly connected to a smartphone, there are things that hapoen on the Web when I&apos;m not paying attention. (Shocking, I know.) IFTTT - short for \"If This Then That\" - has been one of my favorite services to keep tabs on people and companies when I&apos;m not paying rapt attention to Twitter and Facebook.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/print\">print</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/developer\">developer</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/mike\">mike</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/social\">social</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://blog.chron.com/techblog/2012/09/google-may-come-to-the-rescue-of-ios-6-maps-users-if-apple-will-let-it/\">Google may come to the rescue of iOS 6 Maps users - if Apple will let it | TechBlog | a Chron.com blog</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;With iOS 6, Apple severed its most visible ties with Google, dropping the YouTube app altogether and replacing the Maps app with one it developed from scratch.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/rescue\">rescue</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios\">ios</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/maps\">maps</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/users\">users</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/apple\">apple</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/will\">will</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/com\">com</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/blog\">blog</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.fractuslearning.com/2012/09/20/bring-history-to-life-facebook-twitter/\">How to Bring History to Life Using Facebook Timeline and Twitter</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Taking a look at the Stanford project called \"Republic of Letters\" that has digitally tracked the correspondence of Voltaire, Newton, Rousseau in order to see their \"social graph\",Â the idea of social networks and how ideas and news spread has basically stayed the same. Just the speed of information has increased dramatically.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/how to\">how to</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/history\">history</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/life\">life</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/using\">using</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/facebook\">facebook</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/timeline\">timeline</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"https://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/why-wikipedia-does-belong-in-the-classroom.php\">Why Wikipedia Does Belong in the Classroom</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;The proper place of social media in the classroom remains a mystery to most people, with Wikipedia standing as the biggest, baddest new media nemesis of them all.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/wikipedia\">wikipedia</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/classroom\">classroom</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.braintrack.com/blog/2012/09/15-proven-effects-of-parental-involvement-in-schools/\">15 Proven Effects of Parental Involvement in Schools | BrainTrack Blog</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Most parents realize that parental involvement in education is important in some way, but for many, it&apos;s more of a nagging notion than a hard fact. But there are measurable ways that parental involvement in schools can make a difference, from an increase in student academic achievement to benefits for parents and teachers. Read on as we discuss 15 different ways parental involvement helps to improve outcomes for students, schools, and education as a whole.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/proven\">proven</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/effects\">effects</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/parental\">parental</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/schools\">schools</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/blog\">blog</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.edutopia.org/blog/kinect-classroom-andrew-miller\">Kinect in the Classroom | Edutopia</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;One of the most interesting ways game-based learning (GBL) is being implemented is with the use of Microsoft&apos;s Kinect. Kinect specifically is an accessory to the Xbox 360, where motion and gestures control game functions. From sports games, to \"hack and slash,\" the Kinect physically involves the player in gameplay. But why use it in the classroom? And how should you use it in the classroom? Today I present not only a great rationale for use the Kinect in the classroom, but also some specific ideas and resources for doing so.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/kinect\">kinect</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/classroom\">classroom</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/edutopia\">edutopia</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://edudemic.com/2012/09/mural-ly-mind-mapping-tool-waiting/\">Mural.ly May Be The Mind Mapping Tool You&#8217;ve Been Waiting For</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;We&apos;ve been seeing a lot of Pinterest-inspired tools coming out in education technology over the past couple of months. They&apos;re all meant to better organize your digital world. But what if a tool came along that actually wants to intentionally clutter it?&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/mind mapping\">mind mapping</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.edtechmagazine.com/higher/article/2012/09/5-important-technologies-college-professors-should-understand\">5 Important Technologies College Professors Should Understand | EdTech Magazine</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Not all technology is beneficial to learning. Here are a few things to be wary of, and a few to embrace.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/technologies\">technologies</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/college\">college</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/professors\">professors</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/edtech\">edtech</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/magazine\">magazine</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://creattica.com/infographics/twitter-infographics-and-fun-facts/86694\">Twitter Infographics and Fun Facts &#8211; Infographics &#8211; Creattica</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Twitter Infographics and Fun Facts&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/infographics\">infographics</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/fun\">fun</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/facts\">facts</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.neowin.net/news/hps-pc-head-on-windows-8-surface-and-more\">HP&#8217;s PC head on Windows 8, Surface and more &#8211; Neowin</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;HP is still the world&#8217;s biggest maker of Windows-based PCs and the company has a ton of new models coming out on October 26th for the launch of Windows 8, including some touch screen enabled notebooks, a notebook-tablet hybrid and all-in-one PCs.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/head\">head</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/windows\">windows</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/surface\">surface</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/internet/article3921394.ece\">The Hindu : Sci-Tech / Internet : Microsoft fixes security bug in Internet Explorer</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;Microsoft is releasing an update to its Internet Explorer browser to fix a security problem that could expose personal computers to hacking attacks.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/hindu\">hindu</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/internet\">internet</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/microsoft\">microsoft</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/fixes\">fixes</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/security\">security</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/bug\">bug</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/explorer\">explorer</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://fno.org/Sept2012/bravenewlibrarian.html\">The Brave New Librarian</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;In many school districts suffering from budget woes and poor leadership, library staffing has been severely reduced. School librarians must take a bold stance to restore their positions to a fully funded, robust place in the operation of school districts.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/advocacy\">advocacy</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/librarian\">librarian</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/Library\">Library</a></p>\n<ul class=\"diigo-comments\">         </ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://howto.cnet.com/8301-11310_39-57517187-285/how-to-bring-back-google-maps-in-ios-6/?ttag=fbwp\">How to bring back Google Maps in iOS 6 | How To &#8211; CNET</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">&#8220;iOS 6 ushered in a new mapping app, kicking Google Maps off your home screen and straight to the curb. If you find yourself missing Google Maps, there are a few ways to bring it back.&#8221;</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/how to\">how to</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google\">google</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/google maps\">google maps</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/maps\">maps</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/ios\">ios</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/cnet\">cnet</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"diigo-ps\">Posted from <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com&apos;>Diigo</a>. The rest of my favorite links are <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete&apos;>here</a>.</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11078/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11078/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11078&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(500,8,0,'Extending the Territory: From Open Educational Resources to Open Educational Practices','Diigo','http://journals.akoaotearoa.ac.nz/index.php/JOFDL/article/view/64',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>On the theme of moving from access to practice...and ways to measure degree of implementation ...<br /><br />Article by Ulf-Daniel Ehlers in the Journal of Open, Flexible and Distance Learning... &quot;examines the findings of the recent OPAL report Beyond OER: Shifting Focus from Resources to Practices. In doing so, it defines current understanding of open educational resources and open educational practices, and highlights the shift from open content to open practice. The article includes a framework for supporting open educational practices. The conclusions emphasise that open access is a necessary but not sufficient condition for the opening of education, and foreshadows ongoing moves toward changes in educational architectures that promote increased uptake of open educational resources and wider application of open education.&quot; - <small><a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/westdanam&quot; title=&quot;View Dana West&apos;s content in group&quot;>Dana West</a></small></li></ul></p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/MDDE622&quot;>MDDE622</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/OER&quot;>OER</a>, <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/oped12&quot;>oped12</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/westdanam&quot; title=&quot;View Dana West&apos;s content in group&quot;>Dana West</a></p>',1348296844,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sat, 22 Sep 2012 06:49:22 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(501,0,0,'#oped12 http://t.co/jof6PFFK  some remarks on Slip Slicding Away Open in Mooc','twitter','http://twitter.com/JaapSoft/statuses/249399570197524480',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/JaapSoft/statuses/249399570197524480',NULL,NULL,29,'#<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://t.co/jof6PFFK\">http://t.co/jof6PFFK</a> some remarks on Slip Slicding Away Open in Mooc',1348296962,NULL,NULL,'JaapSoft','http://twitter.com/JaapSoft','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 06:47:45 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(502,0,0,'RT @JaapSoft: #oped12 http://t.co/jof6PFFK  some remarks on Slip Slicding Away Open in Mooc','twitter','http://twitter.com/learnwonder/statuses/249417782482063360',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/learnwonder/statuses/249417782482063360',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/JaapSoft\">JaapSoft</a>: #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://t.co/jof6PFFK\">http://t.co/jof6PFFK</a> some remarks on Slip Slicding Away Open in Mooc',1348302004,NULL,NULL,'learnwonder','http://twitter.com/learnwonder','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 08:00:07 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(503,0,0,'All readings/content are &apos;hidden&apos; under the url http://t.co/5jwOFYmu, just change the week# (e.g. week1, week2, week3...) #oped12','twitter','http://twitter.com/FrznGuru/statuses/249417777859944448',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/FrznGuru/statuses/249417777859944448',NULL,NULL,29,'All readings/content are &apos;hidden&apos; under the url <a href=\"http://t.co/5jwOFYmu\">http://t.co/5jwOFYmu</a>, just change the week# (e.g. week1, week2, week3...) #<em>oped12</em>',1348302004,NULL,NULL,'FrznGuru','http://twitter.com/FrznGuru','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 08:00:06 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(504,0,0,'How the Word Gets Out','text/html','http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/22/how-the-word-gets-out/','Computers;Teaching;Education;Read/Write Web;software',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'I&apos;ve been wanting to write this post for a while but didn&apos;t quite know how to do it.Â  But, when I learned about mural.ly this morning, I figured that it was an opportunity to view mural.ly and create the post. &#8230; <a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/22/how-the-word-gets-out/\">Continue reading &#8594;</a><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11075&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348308363,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 09:00:00 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<p>I&apos;ve been wanting to write this post for a while but didn&apos;t quite know how to do it.Â  But, when I learned about <a href=\"http://mural.ly\">mural.ly</a> this morning, I figured that it was an opportunity to view mural.ly and create the post.</p>\n<p>The post I want to write is kind of a graphic organizer to show how a post that I make gets promoted by others on Twitter.Â  I have this theory that the diehard readers use RSS to aggregate the feed from this blog among others.Â  The real diehards will have it emailed to you.Â  The random readers will pick it up with a news service like Flipboard, Zite, Pulse News, News.me, etc. But, I suspect that there&apos;s a certain element that read a Twitter message from someone and then follow a link to get over here.Â  A Retweet is easy to spot with the RT or MT in the message but there are some that are just difficult to trace.</p>\n<p>So, I know a couple of ways that the message gets out because I&apos;m the creator behind that and I&apos;m just going to guess on the rest.</p>\n<p>Yesterday, Shannon Smith gave a terrific interview about her first weeks as principal of Glen Cairn Public School in Ottawa.Â  I&apos;m really appreciative that she found the time in her busy new schedule to take the time for the interview.Â  As I write this, it&apos;s 9:30 on Friday morning and already the word has spread on Twitter about the post.Â  I did some backtracking and found what I hope are all of the mentions of the interview at this point.</p>\n<p>So, I did some screen grabs of the individual Twitter messages and put them into mural.ly to see what I could do.Â  Here&apos;s the result.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/mindmap.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:block;float:none;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;padding-top:0;border:0;\" title=\"mindmap\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/mindmap_thumb.jpg?w=554&h=337\" alt=\"mindmap\" width=\"554\" height=\"337\" border=\"0\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">Click image to see it full size.</p>\n<p>I know that I wrote the original post yesterday and sent it off to WordPress for publishing at 5:00am.Â  I use the <a href=\"http://dlvr.it\">dlvr.it</a> service to do that.Â  I schedule it on WordPress and dlvr.it detects whenever something is posted there and automatically posts an announcement of same to Twitter.Â  It serves me well and beats the heck out of blogging in the middle of the night.Â  Thumbs up.</p>\n<p>I&apos;m not the only robot looking for something new.Â  CanuckEduS monitors many Canadian blogger with Twitterfeed and announces whenever something new is posted.Â  That&apos;s great and reaches a bigger audience.Â  All of these robots do cause some concern because one slip and they&apos;re all over it.Â  You can&apos;t recall a notice once they send it!</p>\n<p>More importantly, real people come along later in the morning.Â  However they get a notice, they&apos;re kind enough to pass along the word of the new post.Â  You&apos;ll notice that there were a few people that were good enough to do that.Â  How they got their notice eludes me but I&apos;m just thankful that they did.</p>\n<p>But enough about me â€“ back to creating the mural, er map.</p>\n<p>Once I have the screen captures as raw materials, it&apos;s a matter of drag/drop or copy/paste to put them into the workplace.Â  Tape an element and you can draw it into place.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/shannon.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:block;float:none;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;padding-top:0;border:0;\" title=\"shannon\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/shannon_thumb.jpg?w=554&h=199\" alt=\"shannon\" width=\"554\" height=\"199\" border=\"0\" /></a></p>\n<p>Each of these images now become an element.Â  Tap to highlight getting the dots for a border around the object and you can pic it up, move it around, or rotate, resize or choose an option from the menu.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/menu.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:block;float:none;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;padding-top:0;border:0;\" title=\"menu\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/menu_thumb.jpg?w=168&h=275\" alt=\"menu\" width=\"168\" height=\"275\" border=\"0\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you&apos;ve ever worked with an interactive whiteboard, you&apos;ll be right at home here.Â  In fact, this may well be your primary memory mapping utility to actually use on your IWB.</p>\n<p>A menu along the left of the screen provides flyouts for the types of actions that you&apos;ll use when editing your mural.Â  In this case, I&apos;ve flown out a sample of the stickers that are available.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/flyout.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:block;float:none;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;padding-top:0;border:0;\" title=\"flyout\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/flyout_thumb.jpg?w=396&h=734\" alt=\"flyout\" width=\"396\" height=\"734\" border=\"0\" /></a></p>\n<p>The last two options are really interesting.Â  There is a show/presentation mode that let you present your ideas to an audience.Â  I found that there&apos;s a really nice selection of tools to do everything that I could think of with a memory map.Â  When you first create a document, you have a choice of public or private which is nice.Â  In fact, I think that most people start private until it gets ready for show time and then make it public or at least provide a link to the document.</p>\n<p>Mural.ly shows its suggested workflow as you log in.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/mural1.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:block;float:none;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;padding-top:0;border:0;\" title=\"mural1\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/mural1_thumb.jpg?w=554&h=185\" alt=\"mural1\" width=\"554\" height=\"185\" border=\"0\" /></a></p>\n<p>The whole process was very easy and you can really get a sense of the power in this tool.Â  There are a good selection of options for sharing once you do decide to go live...</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/options.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:block;float:none;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;padding-top:0;border:0;\" title=\"options\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/options_thumb.jpg?w=205&h=204\" alt=\"options\" width=\"205\" height=\"204\" border=\"0\" /></a></p>\n<p>The link to my project is <a href=\"http://mrl.li/SIi2Q9\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>I found mural.ly very easy and intuitive to work with.Â  Give it a try; I&apos;d be very interested in other opinions on this product.</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11075/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11075/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11075&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(505,0,0,'RT @FrznGuru: All readings/content are &apos;hidden&apos; under the url http://t.co/5jwOFYmu, just change the week# (e.g. week1, week2, week3...)  ...','twitter','http://twitter.com/DimitrisTzouris/statuses/249461294602797056',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/DimitrisTzouris/statuses/249461294602797056',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/FrznGuru\">FrznGuru</a>: All readings/content are &apos;hidden&apos; under the url <a href=\"http://t.co/5jwOFYmu\">http://t.co/5jwOFYmu</a>, just change the week# (e.g. week1, week2, week3...) ...',1348312082,NULL,NULL,'DimitrisTzouris','http://twitter.com/DimitrisTzouris','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 10:53:02 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(506,0,0,'Wh