n Education? | @scoopit http://t.co/xxgDf8Fh #UkrEl11 #mobimooc','twitter','http://twitter.com/bugaychuk/statuses/249524995972272129',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/bugaychuk/statuses/249524995972272129',NULL,NULL,29,'Open Learning is different from Open Education? | @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/scoopit\">scoopit</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/xxgDf8Fh\">http://t.co/xxgDf8Fh</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23UkrEl11\" title=\"#UkrEl11\" class=\" \">#UkrEl11</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23mobimooc\" title=\"#mobimooc\" class=\" \">#mobimooc</a>',1348327203,NULL,NULL,'bugaychuk','http://twitter.com/bugaychuk','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 15:06:09 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(512,0,0,'RT @maryakem: Thx for this! Reminds me of the death of blogs RT @ifrank http://t.co/579LVibx #oped12 #mooc TLTGmooc1#','twitter','http://twitter.com/_valeriei/statuses/249508947743109120',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/_valeriei/statuses/249508947743109120',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/maryakem\">maryakem</a>: Thx for this! Reminds me of the death of blogs RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/ifrank\">ifrank</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/579LVibx\">http://t.co/579LVibx</a> #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23mooc\" title=\"#mooc\" class=\" \">#mooc</a> TLTGmooc1#',1348327203,NULL,NULL,'_valeriei','http://twitter.com/_valeriei','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 14:02:23 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(513,26,0,'Dear Extravert','text/html','http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/2012/09/22/dear-extravert/','Smarter worker;#oped12;connections;extravert;introvert',NULL,NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'My recent introversion posts seem to be appealing to moocers from #oped12, #cck12, #change11, #fslt12 and #ds106. Â Thanks for making time to have a look and/or contribute your perspectives. Â It&#8217;s so nice to feel a growing sense of camaraderie about this topic. As I commented to a follower earlier today, I feel like a minority [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com&#038;blog=27959777&#038;post=742&#038;subd=brainysmurf1234&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348332723,NULL,NULL,'brainysmurf1234','http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 16:33:30 +0000',NULL,'Connecting the dots','15','<p>My recent introversion posts seem to be appealing to moocers from #oped12, #cck12, #change11, #fslt12 and #ds106. Â Thanks for making time to have a look and/or contribute your perspectives. Â It&#8217;s so nice to feel a growing sense of camaraderie about this topic.</p>\n<p>As I commented to a follower earlier today, I feel like a minority voice compelled to speak out against an injustice. Â I do not equate this with the magnitude of destruction caused by racism, homophobia, religious extremism or other pervasive forms of discrimination. Â I just think that being judged for my natural temperament as being &#8216;less than&#8217; feels wrong and I&#8217;m ready to challenge it.</p>\n<p>This is part one of two&#8230;Dear Introvert will follow, I promise, because I am thinking of each group in tandem. Â I&#8217;m also going to leave this more raw and exposed than I normally would to allow for push-back and dialogue to shape it into greater understanding.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://brainysmurf1234.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/img473.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-743\" title=\"Sailboat\" src=\"http://brainysmurf1234.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/img473.jpg?w=238&h=158\" alt=\"\" width=\"238\" height=\"158\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Dear Extravert:</strong></p>\n<p>This is a long letter so please honour the time and effort I put into it by hanging in there and reading every word to the end, even if it feels a bit awkward.</p>\n<p>I would be so pleased if you did not come rushing into my office first thing in the morning, talking a mile a minute, asking how my weekend was and then not really sticking with the topic for too long before telling me about how your weekend was. Â I&#8217;m sure your interest in sharing comes from a kind-hearted place but I&#8217;m not awake yet and the last thing I need is someone barging into my quiet little cubicle in this open office while I&#8217;m trying to gather my thoughts and get organized to start my day. Â I don&#8217;t bounce out of bed all joyful about the world and its potential. Â I&#8217;m cautious, reserved and I&#8217;m saving my limited time and energy for my handful of priorities, which I have spent considerable time sorting out before I even walked in here today.</p>\n<p>I don&#8217;t like spewing my personal stuff at work, anyway. Â I&#8217;m very private and very mindful of others who may be listening, for whom my life is none of their business. Â I wish you would notice and respect that about me. Â Your need to interact and share everything is *not* more important than my need for quiet and privacy. Â Being on is as life-affirming for you as being off is for me.</p>\n<p>Please percolate on that.</p>\n<p>Slow down, digest it, figure out what it means *for me* and for the other introverts in your personal and professional life. Â Otherwise, don&#8217;t be surprised when I (we) come off as dismissive, cold, uninterested or whatever other negative attributions you want to assign to my (our) reactions.</p>\n<p>I don&#8217;t want to be rude to you. Â I don&#8217;t want to debate or explain or validate what you need when you come running in here. Â This is about what I need and, with increasing velocity and determination lately, I am taking charge of my needs and not accepting any less.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m a really good listener, I know that. Â You probably know that, too, and that&#8217;s why you seem eager to see me and tell me everything that&#8217;s going on in your fast-paced life that can appear overly dramatic to me. Â You know I&#8217;m patient. Â You know I&#8217;m analytical and excellent at synthesizing so I may offer some insights that you haven&#8217;t been able to figure out yet. Â Please, just step back for a sec and realize that you&#8217;re coming at me full of *your* needs: your need to &#8216;get high&#8217; on connecting, your need to crank yourself up for the day, your need to be heard, your stories, your boundless energy.</p>\n<p>What about my need for space, for time to reflect, for being asked questions that have depth and meaning? Â Oh wait, I forgot to explain that upfront: I don&#8217;t enjoy casual chit-chat. Â  It&#8217;s a waste of my time. Â It doesn&#8217;t offer me anything I haven&#8217;t heard a thousand times already on the bus, in the street, on the news or on the web.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m bored by repetition and superficiality. Â Give me something golden to run with, a problem to solve or some dots to connect, something that respects the value of my time and my unique contribution. See if you could come to me for me, not for you.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m private. Â I&#8217;m a tough nut to crack. Â You have to earn the keys to the safe.</p>\n<p>Could you please come to me and stick with what *I* was talking about, not shifting back to you mid-sentence, and maybe we&#8217;ll both get what we need more often? Â I see you making this enormous effort to try and ask me more about me sometimes and the fact that you have to try so very hard and then can&#8217;t stick with it makes the whole interaction distasteful and tiring. Â I don&#8217;t know what to do about that. Â I&#8217;ve tried to talk to you about it, when I could get a word in edgewise, but it doesn&#8217;t seem to change anything so I withdraw a little further.</p>\n<p>I now know, from reading up on <a href=\"http://www.thepowerofintroverts.com\" target=\"_blank\">the power of introverts</a>, that it&#8217;s not natural for you to be aware of these intricacies of human interaction and quality conversation, to pick up on all the non-verbal cues and read between the lines. Â You weren&#8217;t born that way and you may not have been given the constructive feedback needed to develop these skills as you matured because you could always find like-minded extraverts to play with or other introverts who would listen more patiently, whether they genuinely wanted to or not.</p>\n<p>You like shiny things, fun things, and all this meta-analytical awareness and attention to detail bores you to tears and makes you tired. Â I get that. Â I&#8217;m the one who picks up on this stuff, remember? Â What&#8217;s changed is that I&#8217;m tired of indulging what you need. Â This ain&#8217;t about you anymore and you&#8217;re not going to like that. Â We may part ways over this and I&#8217;m okay with that now. Â I know what I need and I&#8217;m getting it elsewhere, in person and online, often asynchronously and with much greater understanding and authenticity, which feels effortless and liberating.</p>\n<p>These are exciting times for me and, consequently, I&#8217;m not as available to you as I once was. Â You know where to reach me, if and when you discover how to offer what I need and how I need it.</p>\n<p>I know this is a lot to take in. Â Thank you for making the time.</p>\n<br /> Tagged: <a href=&apos;http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/tag/oped12/&apos;>#oped12</a>, <a href=&apos;http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/tag/connections/&apos;>connections</a>, <a href=&apos;http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/tag/extravert/&apos;>extravert</a>, <a href=&apos;http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/tag/introvert/&apos;>introvert</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/742/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/742/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com&#038;blog=27959777&#038;post=742&#038;subd=brainysmurf1234&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(514,0,0,'Openness and me this week','text/html','http://maryakem.wordpress.com/2012/09/22/openness-and-me-this-week/','Uncategorized',NULL,NULL,22,NULL,NULL,NULL,38,'I continue to rush through a few jobs to working my OiE work, next month WILL be better I promise. For this week I have to rest on my fear that after 10 years in teaching, learning, libraries and education my posture here appears to reflect my overall attitude as a&#8230; pundit.Â  Oh golly! I [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=maryakem.wordpress.com&#038;blog=40387844&#038;post=22&#038;subd=maryakem&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348346043,NULL,NULL,'maryakem','http://maryakem.wordpress.com','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 20:07:51 +0000',NULL,'Openness in Education Blog by maryakem',NULL,'<p>I continue to rush through a few jobs to working my OiE work, next month WILL be better I promise.</p>\n<p>For this week I have to rest on my fear that after 10 years in teaching, learning, libraries and education my posture here appears to reflect my overall attitude as a&#8230; pundit.Â  Oh golly!</p>\n<p>I would really rather be reading and commenting again this week than blogging myself so I will head off to engage with everyone on #opened12 right after this .. but it&#8217;s not like i have done nothing this week.</p>\n<p>1. I spent hours preparing lessons for students at my University with more aspects of retro-librarianship than I like.Â  My gut quavering in fear that MPOW is so ingratiated to the resource economy that we are still saying use this scholarly resource when we mean.. prefer a proprietary one!Â  One of our fellows here raised that.. I&#8217;ll go comment over there&#8230; stand by&#8230;</p>\n<p>2. I attended the event from <a title=\"Big Ideas Libraries in Communities\" href=\"http://www.sfu.ca/publicsquare/community-summit/summit-events/libraries-in-communities.html\">Simon Fraser University</a> Called big ideas for libraries in communities.Â  10 persons, not necessarily librarians (phew), each had 5min to present ideas to embed libraries in community.. which is of course a euphemism for increase relevance of [insert your demi-victorian-waning-socialwelfare-public service here]&#8230;. In the top 3 audience picks were libraries supporting rare, unique publications; digitization of local photographs on an open platform; #mooc for digital literacy for citizens from the public library.Â  I could write a paper on the politic, economics and sociology (never mind the history ; >) of open education embedded in the dialogue there.Â  Maybe I&#8217;ll do that&#8230; soon. #wishfulthinking</p>\n<p>3. I was engaged yesterday in the <a href=\"https://twitter.com//search/opendataLS\">#opendataLS</a> Open Data Learning Summit from the BC government and the BC Libraries CO-op.Â  One more heartbreaking conference where the potential of some great leap forward is envisioned within a crippling silo of likeminded people.Â  I have a really strong track record with that, which is made even stronger by participating in the business of K12 education, Higher ed, public libraries, IT service and gov&#8217;t at one turn or another over the last 18 months.Â  Like I say&#8230; heartbreaking&#8230; but still we try.</p>\n<p>I think especially of the question from the remarkable journalist and coder <a href=\"http://twitter.com/coppinr\">@coppinr</a> can libraries be aggregating data sets in the spirit of openness.Â  We didn&#8217;t admit it.. but the answer is no.Â  IT service management and libraries is more than often a disaster, library skills with collection management is something that is at odds with technical services sustainability and the tenor of datasets so although we keep saying we&#8217;ll change this any day&#8230;Â  we are NOT there yet.Â  Our service mode is sustaining too many old services to offer these new ones..</p>\n<p>Please go visit the archives&#8230;instead! Where they might be smidge better off infrastructure wise but will lack the opennesses you sense so rightly from public libraries.. or worse yet leave publics for &#8216;the university&#8217; where brand and ownership will infect datasets to their very core within minutes :<</p>\n<p>Thank youÂ  <a href=\"http://twitter.com/coppinr\">Rhiannon CoppinÂ </a> your question is so important.</p>\n<p>And a thank you too, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/haigarmen\">@haigarman</a> for his data visualization talk and math + aesthetics advocacy.Â  A wonderful after talk with him about the painful history of literacy over numeracy in the North American psyche&#8230;Â  I could probably write a thesis on &#8220;the language of instruction&#8221; how literacy and the tyranny of books kill collaboration, innovation and equity in learning extended Canadian edition #ohcanada #languagefight</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/maryakem.wordpress.com/22/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/maryakem.wordpress.com/22/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=maryakem.wordpress.com&#038;blog=40387844&#038;post=22&#038;subd=maryakem&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(515,0,0,'Open Learning is different from Open Edu&#x2026; http://t.co/na5eNIBC #ukrel11','twitter','http://twitter.com/kukharenko/statuses/249592950529617921',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/kukharenko/statuses/249592950529617921',NULL,NULL,29,'Open Learning is different from Open Edu&#x2026; <a href=\"http://t.co/na5eNIBC\">http://t.co/na5eNIBC</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23ukrel11\" title=\"#ukrel11\" class=\" \">#ukrel11</a>',1348347363,NULL,NULL,'kukharenko','http://twitter.com/kukharenko','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 19:36:11 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(516,0,0,'Open online content - a puzzle of definitions to sort out.  #oped12','twitter','http://twitter.com/Olliemydog/statuses/249651291985416192',NULL,NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/Olliemydog/statuses/249651291985416192',NULL,NULL,29,'Open online content - a puzzle of definitions to sort out. #<em>oped12</em>',1348357443,NULL,NULL,'Olliemydog','http://twitter.com/Olliemydog','Sat, 22 Sep 2012 23:28:00 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(517,0,0,'Reshared post from Gandhi:','text/html','https://plus.google.com/110117137800261731479/posts/BGJ7emQLoVs',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,'<hr/><p><strong><a href=&apos;https://plus.google.com/100968180704537546357/posts/17rva6vN3Qh&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Original Post</a> from <a href=&apos;https://plus.google.com/100968180704537546357&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;>Gandhi</a>:</strong></p><p></p><p class=&apos;attachment photo&apos;>\n										<a href=&apos;https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-27YJKtWg6_8/UF3tSdPynjI/AAAAAAAAMfo/ZBkB4-ELKL4/s0-d/be%2Bthe%2Bchange%2Byou%2Bwish%2Bto%2Bsee%2Bin%2Bthe%2Bworld%2Bgandhi%2B2.jpg&apos; target=&apos;_blank&apos;><img src=&apos;https://images0-focus-opensocial.googleusercontent.com/gadgets/proxy?container=focus&gadget=a&resize_h=100&url=https%3A%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2F-27YJKtWg6_8%2FUF3tSdPynjI%2FAAAAAAAAMfo%2FZBkB4-ELKL4%2Fs0-d%2Fbe%252Bthe%252Bchange%252Byou%252Bwish%252Bto%252Bsee%252Bin%252Bthe%252Bworld%252Bgandhi%252B2.jpg&apos; height=&apos;100&apos;/> be the change you wish t