ULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(676,0,0,'Pinterest to Focus on a Topic','text/html','http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/26/pinterest-to-focus-on-a-topic/','application;Education;Read/Write Web;Digital storytelling;Geographic information system;Google;Pinterest;Services;Social Sciences;Twitter;category',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'Many people think of Pinterest as a great place for pinning recipes and fashions. Â Goodness knows that so many people do and enjoy that. Â You can find Pinterest boards for any taste and desire. But, educators are also using this as a way to share resources for particular topics. Â It lets them focus on a [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11123&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348651443,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Wed, 26 Sep 2012 09:00:00 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<p>Many people think of Pinterest as a great place for pinning recipes and fashions. Â Goodness knows that so many people do and enjoy that. Â You can find Pinterest boards for any taste and desire.</p>\n<p>But, educators are also using this as a way to share resources for particular topics. Â It lets them focus on a theme and, at the same time, give the potential visitor a visual and text preview of what to expect should you click-through to the resource.</p>\n<p>I ran across a couple of very interesting boards today and I&#8217;d like to share them in this post. Â I think that they are good examples of what can be done in the world of sharing.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/shellyterrell/digital-storytelling/\">Digital Storytelling<br />\n</a></strong>Shelly Terrell has assembled a nice selection of resources devoted to storytelling in the digital world.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/shelly1.png?w=500&h=237\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"237\" /></p>\n<p>Sometimes people amass collections to try to have &#8220;every resource known to the digital universe&#8221;. Â When you do that and share it for others to use, they can be overwhelmed by the resource.</p>\n<p>In this case, Shelly has condensed the collection to 15 pins that should serve anyone interested in digital storytelling well.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/petemcas/gis-ideas-for-k-12/\">GIS Ideas for K-12<br />\n</a></strong>Peter McAsh reminds all the time that he&#8217;s a Geography educator first and Computer Studies educator second! Â At this year&#8217;s Educational Computing Organization of Ontario&#8217;s Annual Conference, Peter has paired himself with James Lockyer to get people to<strong> <a href=\"http://lanyrd.com/2012/ecoo12/swbpk/\">think outside the Geography box when using GIS</a></strong>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"http://dougpete.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/peter.png?w=500\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n<p>To support his session, Peter has put together a similar number of resources of ideas for GIS in the K-12 classroom.</p>\n<p>If I can, I may just wander by that session to see what he&#8217;s up to.</p>\n<p>I like what Shelly and Peter are doing with Pinterest. Â It&#8217;s an updated way to share links and resources with other professionals. Â It is very easy to read and use and should serve their purposes well. Â I think both are good examples of why educators need to keep their minds open to new innovation in the online world. Â The next great thing will only be great if you embrace it and put it through its paces. Â You can&#8217;t do that by continuing to do the same old, same old.</p>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size:1em;\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul\">\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.prdaily.com/SocialMedia/Articles/e9941c69-3571-423e-8c05-6b9d1697886b.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">How Pinterest can boost your press release results</a> (prdaily.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://attipscast.com/2012/09/16/sneak-peek-digital-storytelling-sample/\" target=\"_blank\">Sneak Peek: Digital Storytelling Sample</a> (attipscast.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.pinterestinsider.com/2012/09/a-ceos-guide-to-pinterest-infographic.html\" target=\"_blank\">A CEO&#8217;s Guide to Pinterest (Infographic)</a> (pinterestinsider.com)</li>\n</ul>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11123/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11123/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11123&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(677,17,0,'Open and sharing public funded resources #oped12 #opedk12','text/html','http://connectiv.wordpress.com/2012/09/26/open-and-sharing-public-funded-resources-oped12-opedk12/','open education;category',NULL,NULL,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,57,'&#8221; From my perspective resources developed with public funds should be accessible by the public. Journals publishing research funded by the government should be open. Content/curriculum created by public institutions should be made public. Additionally, education has been listed as one of the primary determinants of life expectancy, reduction of poverty, &#8221; (George Siemens) Wikiwijs [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=connectiv.wordpress.com&#038;blog=19220396&#038;post=2102&#038;subd=connectiv&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348660805,NULL,NULL,'jaapsoft2','http://connectiv.wordpress.com','Wed, 26 Sep 2012 10:37:31 +0000',NULL,'connectiv','12','<p><a href=\"http://connectiv.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/delen-is-vermenigvuldigen.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2114\" title=\"Delen-is-vermenigvuldigen\" src=\"http://connectiv.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/delen-is-vermenigvuldigen.png?w=620\" alt=\"\"  /></a>&#8221; From my perspective resources developed with public funds should be accessible by the public. Journals publishing research funded by the government should be open. Content/curriculum created by public institutions should be made public. Additionally, education has been listed as one of the primary determinants of life expectancy, reduction of poverty, &#8221; <a href=\"http://www.connectivism.ca/?p=111\" target=\"_blank\">(George Siemens)</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wikiwijs.nl/task/international.psml\" target=\"_blank\">Wikiwijs</a> is the OER-projec in the Netherlands used by all levels of education.<br />\nTeachers in the Netherlands use open educaional materials 65% in universities and 47% in primairy schools (4-12) (<a href=\"http://openserviceblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/onderzoeksrapportage-wikwijs-20123.pdf\">Onderzoek Wikiwijs 2012</a>) Â OER in the Netherlands is a national project.</p>\n<p>The key question is how can you set things up so there is both an ego reward and a formal reward for learning output to be shared?\" <a href=\"http:// www.dlib.org/dlib/march05/kraan/03kraan.html\" target=\"_blank\">(Kraan / Mason 2005)</a> cit. in <a href=\"http://www.olcos.org/cms/upload/docs/olcos_roadmap.pdf\">Olcos Roadmap</a> [pdf]</p>\n<p>In some countries (like USA and UK) public education is almost the same as mediocre and not-for-my-child education. The better educationÂ in those countries is very expensive. Â In my view that causes an evil split in society.</p>\n<p>Public funded educational materials should be open, why should non-public or commercial educational institutions deliver their materials to the open?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/connectiv.wordpress.com/2102/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/connectiv.wordpress.com/2102/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=connectiv.wordpress.com&#038;blog=19220396&#038;post=2102&#038;subd=connectiv&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(678,0,0,'I vote for $MOOC MT @ifrank: If MOOCs charging for certificates, call them $MOOCs? or drop \"open\"  $MOC? #oped12 #TLTGmooc1  #mooc','twitter','http://twitter.com/shermandorn/statuses/250934947467100160','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/shermandorn/statuses/250934947467100160',NULL,NULL,29,'I vote for $MOOC MT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/ifrank\">ifrank</a>: If MOOCs charging for certificates, call them $MOOCs? or drop \"open\" $MOC? #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23TLTGmooc1\" title=\"#TLTGmooc1\" class=\" \">#TLTGmooc1</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23mooc\" title=\"#mooc\" class=\" \">#mooc</a>',1348663570,NULL,NULL,'shermandorn','http://twitter.com/shermandorn','Wed, 26 Sep 2012 12:28:48 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(679,0,0,'If some MOOCs start charging for certificates, etc, will we call them $MOOCs? Or just drop the \"open\".  $MOC ? #oped12 #TLTGmooc1  #mooc','twitter','http://twitter.com/ifrank/statuses/250933790162165760','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/ifrank/statuses/250933790162165760',NULL,NULL,29,'If some MOOCs start charging for certificates, etc, will we call them $MOOCs? Or just drop the \"open\". $MOC ? #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23TLTGmooc1