ne, il 30 prossimo chiuderÃ  i battenti, Ã¨ tempoÂ  che io faccia un bilancio di questa mia nuova esperienza di cMOOC. Non nego che la sua conclusione affievolisce il senso di insoddisfazione che mi ha accompagnato in queste settimane, un&#8217;inquietudine dovuta al fatto che non sono riuscita a interagire in modo conforme a quanto preventivato. Mi rimprovero di essermi lasciata disturbare dagli aggiornamenti giornalieri relativi ai forum di discussione a cui mi sono iscritta, ipotizzando di essere in grado di interagire fluidamente. CosÃ¬ non Ã¨ stato pur non essendo mancata l&#8217;interazione attraverso questo mio blog, la condivisione di risorse col gruppo mobimooc su Facebooc, qualche intervento in lingua inglese nel forum di discussione globale. Non dimenticoÂ  lo scoglio della lingua che in questo contesto ha fatto sentire maggiormente la sua influenza inibitoria.</p>\n<p>Nonostante ciÃ² mi ritengo soddisfatta per l&#8217;apprendimento acquisito e soprattutto per lo squarcio operato nel pianeta mobile learning cheÂ  pregiudizialmente avevo ritenuto a me precluso.</p>\n<p>SÃ¬, #mobimooc12 si Ã¨ rivelato una valida bussola.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://serenaturri.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/200px-compass_icon_matte-svg.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-2188 aligncenter\" title=\"200px-Compass_icon_matte.svg\" src=\"http://serenaturri.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/200px-compass_icon_matte-svg.png?w=200&h=179\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"179\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">fonte <a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Compass_icon_matte.svg?uselang=it\">wikimedia</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\n<p>Ora potrÃ² dedicarmi a tempo pieno a #oped12, in attesa dell&#8217;avvio di #CFHE12.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Post correlati (in ordine cronologico)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/2012/08/09/esplorazione-degli-spazi-di-mobimooc/\">Esplorazione degli spazi diÂ #mobiMOOC</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/2012/08/19/mobimooc-condivisione-dei-segnalibri-tramite-delicious/\">#mobiMOOC12: condivisione dei segnalibri tramiteÂ Delicious</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2082&amp;action=edit\">#mobiMOOC12: gruppo Google</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/2012/09/06/mobimooc-introducing-myself/\">#mobiMooc, IntroducingÂ myself</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/2012/09/08/mobimooc-the-basic-concepts/\">#mobiMooc, The basicÂ concepts</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/2012/09/10/mobimooc2012-possible-or-probable/\">#mobiMooc2012, Possible orÂ probable?</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://serenaturri.wordpress.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2136&amp;action=edit\">#mobimooc2012, Sulla condivisione degli strumenti mobili e sul curriculum mlearning</a></p>\n<br />Filed under: <a href=&apos;http://serenaturri.wordpress.com/category/mobimooc/&apos;>mobiMOOC</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/serenaturri.wordpress.com/2185/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/serenaturri.wordpress.com/2185/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=serenaturri.wordpress.com&#038;blog=9618855&#038;post=2185&#038;subd=serenaturri&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(759,3,0,'Pontydysgu â€“ Bridge to Learning - Educational Research','Diigo','http://www.pontydysgu.org/2012/09/guidance-on-ebooks/','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/tag/no_tag&quot;>no_tag</a></p><p><strong>by:</strong> <a href=&quot;http://groups.diigo.com/group/oped12/content/user/helenaca&quot; title=&quot;View Helena Capela&apos;s content in group&quot;>Helena Capela</a></p>',1348866365,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fri, 28 Sep 2012 19:42:11 -0000',NULL,'Best content in oped12 | Diigo - Groups','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(760,0,0,'Copyright and power #oped12 powerful readings and viewings in the course, gets you thinking - http://t.co/G6QIwuNJ','twitter','http://twitter.com/jgh/statuses/251784171310182401','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/jgh/statuses/251784171310182401',NULL,NULL,29,'Copyright and power #<em>oped12</em> powerful readings and viewings in the course, gets you thinking - <a href=\"http://t.co/G6QIwuNJ\">http://t.co/G6QIwuNJ</a>',1348866483,NULL,NULL,'jgh','http://twitter.com/jgh','Fri, 28 Sep 2012 20:43:19 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(761,0,0,'MY @daveandcori: California universities to produce 50 open-source textbooks http://t.co/DheGjZmf #edchat #edtech #textbooks #oped12','twitter','http://twitter.com/SussexTLDU/statuses/251783084456939520','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/SussexTLDU/statuses/251783084456939520',NULL,NULL,29,'MY @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/daveandcori\">daveandcori</a>: California universities to produce 50 open-source textbooks <a href=\"http://t.co/DheGjZmf\">http://t.co/DheGjZmf</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23edchat\" title=\"#edchat\" class=\" \">#edchat</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23edtech\" title=\"#edtech\" class=\" \">#edtech</a> <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23textbooks\" title=\"#textbooks\" class=\" \">#textbooks</a> #<em>oped12</em>',1348866483,NULL,NULL,'SussexTLDU','http://twitter.com/SussexTLDU','Fri, 28 Sep 2012 20:38:59 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(762,11,0,'Copyright and power','text/html','http://edtech-insights.blogspot.com/2012/09/copyright-and-power.html','#oped12;category',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-28 14:41:24',11,'The readings and viewings for #oped12 on openness in education Week 3 get you thinking.<br />After watching the excellent <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/8040182\" target=\"_blank\">RiP: the Remix Manifesto</a> by Laurent LaSalle, I turned to G+ and found a What&apos;s Hot item. Except I could not see it. I saw this instead:<br /><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/--R2PIFD80sA/UGYGPpa_MII/AAAAAAABJQU/k6VE3jtfaLo/s1600/no+longer+available.PNG\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"403\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/--R2PIFD80sA/UGYGPpa_MII/AAAAAAABJQU/k6VE3jtfaLo/s640/no+longer+available.PNG\" width=\"640\" /></a><br />Samuel L. Jackson&apos;s<a href=\"http://creativity-online.com/work/jewish-council-for-education-and-research-wtfu/29328\" target=\"_blank\"> WTFU</a> campaign for Obama had been taken down due to a copyright claim by JCER. Could this be the Jewish Council for Education and Research, the same group that produced the advert? Don&apos;t know.<br />But why are they objecting to a showing of their advertisement? Surely that is the point of an advert - getting maximum air time.<br />There are <a href=\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/celebrities/7743676/Samuel-L-Jackson-Wake-the-F-ck-Up\" target=\"_blank\">other places</a> to see it, of course. <br />The Remix Manifesto and Lawrence Lessig&apos;s <a href=\"http://randomfoo.net/oscon/2002/lessig/free.html\" target=\"_blank\">Free Culture</a> (another viewing for the course - free as in free-up, or no cost, but not OPEN, a more recent term, perhaps), are thought-provoking. The early Walt Disney mash-ups done in true open style, when contrasted with the demonic protection of that same Disney material later, illustrate so well the use of commercial power. This power has stifled creativity and affected random individuals in a way totally disproportionate to the individual harm done. And the strong arm tactic of governments is felt throughout the world on this issue. <br /><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5256199820880743341-8287289342456711302?l=edtech-insights.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',1348867323,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fri, 28 Sep 2012 20:41:00 +0000',NULL,'EdTech -  Insights','9','The readings and viewings for #oped12 on openness in education Week 3 get you thinking.<br />After watching the excellent <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/8040182\" target=\"_blank\">RiP: the Remix Manifesto</a> by Laurent LaSalle, I turned to G+ and found a What&apos;s Hot item. Except I could not see it. I saw this instead:<br /><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/--R2PIFD80sA/UGYGPpa_MII/AAAAAAABJQU/k6VE3jtfaLo/s1600/no+longer+available.PNG\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"403\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/--R2PIFD80sA/UGYGPpa_MII/AAAAAAABJQU/k6VE3jtfaLo/s640/no+longer+available.PNG\" width=\"640\" /></a><br />Samuel L. Jackson&apos;s<a href=\"http://creativity-online.com/work/jewish-council-for-education-and-research-wtfu/29328\" target=\"_blank\"> WTFU</a> campaign for Obama had been taken down due to a copyright claim by JCER. Could this be the Jewish Council for Education and Research, the same group that produced the advert? Don&apos;t know.<br />But why are they objecting to a showing of their advertisement? Surely that is the point of an advert - getting maximum air time.<br />There are <a href=\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/celebrities/7743676/Samuel-L-Jackson-Wake-the-F-ck-Up\" target=\"_blank\">other places</a> to see it, of course. <br />The Remix Manifesto and Lawrence Lessig&apos;s <a href=\"http://randomfoo.net/oscon/2002/lessig/free.html\" target=\"_blank\">Free Culture</a> (another viewing for the course - free as in free-up, or no cost, but not OPEN, a more recent term, perhaps), are thought-provoking. The early Walt Disney mash-ups done in true open style, when contrasted with the demonic protection of that same Disney material later, illustrate so well the use of commercial power. This power has stifled creativity and affected random individuals in a way totally disproportionate to the individual harm done. And the strong arm tactic of governments is felt throughout the world on this issue. <br /><img width=&apos;1&apos; height=&apos;1&apos; src=&apos;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/5256199820880743341-8287289342456711302?l=edtech-insights.blogspot.com&apos; alt=&apos;&apos; />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(763,0,0,'@_valeriei sorry I missed you on  #oped12 last night.. will have to read through later.  how did I miss that.. oh yeah, #teaching','twitter','http://twitter.com/maryakem/statuses/251802939419684865','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/maryakem/statuses/251802939419684865',NULL,NULL,29,'@<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/_valeriei\">_valeriei</a> sorry I missed you on #<em>oped12</em> last night.. will have to read through later. how did I miss that.. oh yeah, <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23teaching\" title=\"#teaching\" class=\" \">#teaching</a>',1348873563,NULL,NULL,'maryakem','http://twitter.com/maryakem','Fri, 28 Sep 2012 21:57:53 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(764,0,0,'RT @gsiemens: RT @courosa: \"The Course in MOOC\" by @downes http://t.co/tczB4tjz Relevant to #etmooc #unmooc discussions. #mooc &amp;amp; #oped12','twitter','http://twitter.com/AnneHole/statuses/251790454155247616','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/AnneHole/statuses/251790454155247616',NULL,NULL,29,'RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/gsiemens\">gsiemens</a>: RT @<a class=\" \" href=\"https://twitter.com/courosa