">via:packrati.us</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/interview\">interview</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/aviva\">aviva</a>      <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/aviva dunsiger\">aviva dunsiger</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\"diigo-link\">        <a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/28/otr-links-09282012/?utm_source=dlvr.it&amp;utm_medium=twitter&amp;utm_campaign=dougpete\">OTR Links 09/28/2012 Â« doug â€“ off the record</a>   </p>\n<p class=\"diigo-description\">Just blogged&#8230; OTR Links 09/28/2012 http://t.co/osMDwDMv</p>\n<p class=\"diigo-tags\">     tags:           <a href=\"http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete/via:packrati.us\">via:packrati.us</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"diigo-ps\">Posted from <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com&apos;>Diigo</a>. The rest of my favorite links are <a href=&apos;http://www.diigo.com/user/dougpete&apos;>here</a>.</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11154/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11154/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11154&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(767,1,0,'Why open?  (this blogpost is a work in progress)','text/html','http://connectiv.wordpress.com/2012/09/29/why-open/','change11;critical thinking;open education;philosophy;questions;closed;open;category',NULL,NULL,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,57,'Why should I throw my intellectual products out in the open? Why do people think open is better than closed? I know most open software is better than closed, but is there a better reason than that for choosing the Open? Find an ethical or philosophical reason for choosing Open. (This is my homework for [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=connectiv.wordpress.com&#038;blog=19220396&#038;post=2119&#038;subd=connectiv&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348905843,NULL,NULL,'jaapsoft2','http://connectiv.wordpress.com','Sat, 29 Sep 2012 06:42:10 +0000',NULL,'connectiv','1','<p><a href=\"http://connectiv.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/homework.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2131\" title=\"homework\" src=\"http://connectiv.files.wordpress.com/2012/09/homework.jpg?w=300&h=232\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"232\" /></a></p>\n<p>Why should I throw my intellectual products out in the open?</p>\n<p>Why do people think open is better than closed?</p>\n<p>I know most open software is better than closed, but is there a better reason than that for choosing the Open?<br />\nFind an ethical or philosophical reason for choosing Open. </p>\n<p>(This is my homework for this weekend, next week will show an answer)</p>\n<p>Is it because sharing is human?</p>\n<p>Is it because solidarity is an ethical rule? <<a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/gnu/manifesto.html\">GNU manifesto</a><br />\nIs it based on the Golden Rule? <<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Golden_Rule\">Golden Rule</a><br />\nIt is an approach that responds to the concerns of others not out of a sense of duty, but from a feeling of responsive mutuality?<br />\nIs &#8220;Property&#8221; a difficult thing? Is it the nature of property that forbids to add knowledge to the list of properties? (<<a href=\"http://www.benthamscience.com/open/toj/articles/V003/28TOJ.pdf\">Property, Bodies and Wittgenstien)</a></p>\n<p>Is copyright used as <<a href=\"http://edtech-insights.blogspot.nl/2012/09/copyright-and-power.html\">censorship?</a>. Keeping people from knowledge? </p>\n<p>(image fromÂ http://marylandlearninglinks.org/)</p>\n<p>Sources:<br />\nBerry (2004) Internet Ethics: Privacy, Ethics and Alienation â€“ <a href=\"http://flosshub.org/sites/flosshub.org/files/berry2.pdf\">An Open Source Approach. (PDF file)</a></p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/connectiv.wordpress.com/2119/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/connectiv.wordpress.com/2119/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=connectiv.wordpress.com&#038;blog=19220396&#038;post=2119&#038;subd=connectiv&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(768,0,0,'Really Using Web 2.0','text/html','http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/29/really-using-web-2-0/','Just Rambling;category',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'This will be a multi-step post of things to do. First, you need to watch this video. Â It&#8217;s not your typical 2 minutes YouTube fare. Hopefully, that&#8217;s one of the most inspirational 11 minutes you&#8217;ve spent online. So, what are the implications? Â After all, you or your school have a website. Â It may be just [...]<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11150&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',1348910283,NULL,NULL,'dougpete','http://dougpete.wordpress.com','Sat, 29 Sep 2012 09:00:24 +0000',NULL,'doug - off the record',NULL,'<p>This will be a multi-step post of things to do.</p>\n<p>First, you need to watch this video. Â It&#8217;s not your typical 2 minutes YouTube fare.</p>\n<a href=\"http://dougpete.wordpress.com/2012/09/29/really-using-web-2-0/\"><img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/fiGabUBQEnM/2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a>\n<p>Hopefully, that&#8217;s one of the most inspirational 11 minutes you&#8217;ve spent online.</p>\n<p>So, what are the implications? Â After all, you or your school have a website. Â It may be just a template with your school colours but you&#8217;re on the web. Â You&#8217;re telling your parents and your students your staff list and bell times. Â If that makes you feel good, then you need to next read this post from George Couros. Â It&#8217;s entitled &#8220;<strong><a title=\"Don&apos;t use 2.0 technology in a 1.0 way\" href=\"http://smartblogs.com/education/2012/09/26/dont-use-2-0-technology-1-0-way/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Don&apos;t use 2.0 technology in a 1.0 way</a></strong>&#8220;.</p>\n<p>Maybe, it&#8217;s time to step away from the keyboard and think this through carefully.</p>\n<p>As a basis for a discussion, I&#8217;d like to consider the classroom instruction &#8220;I want you to do a Powerpoint&#8221;. Â Is that even 1.0? Â Well, you could be using your SkyDrive account. Â And, if this is a class on how to use Powerpoint, it might be appropriate. Â But, is the real instruction &#8220;I want you to create a presentation&#8221;. Â That sheds a whole new light on the discussion. Â Your third step is to read this post. Â <strong><a href=\"http://www.fluency21.com/blogpost.cfm?blogID=2980\">8 Unique Online Presentation Tools for Students</a></strong>. Â I know that I read somewhere that someone found these &#8220;# ways to&#8221; as being lazy. Â Maybe it&#8217;s time to think that it instead, multiple offerings could serve as a vehicle to open a lot of doors.</p>\n<p>Is it necessary that students know all 8? Â No, but what if they did or could or would given the opportunity. Â Maybe they would find a tool that is more attractive to them or more suitableÂ for the delivery of their message? Â What is the ultimate expectation &#8211; that students create a Powerpoint presentation for their presentation or that students create a presentation for their presentation? Â What does opening the door to other web2.0 technologies offer? Â Easy integration of media for their message, online collaboration with their friends, sharing and feedback before, during or after the presentation. Â Does it not make sense?</p>\n<p>So, let&#8217;s head back to your or your school&#8217;s web presence and think about George&#8217;s thoughts. Â Does it take you where you need it to go? Â Is it just a dispenser of information? Â Or, is it more of a conversation? Â Think about your classroom activities. Â Do the same principles apply? Â I think that George&#8217;s post should really make you think and wonder just how effectively you are using things?</p>\n<p>John Seely Brown will appear as a keynote and panel discussion member at the <strong><a href=\"http://www.ecoo.org\">ECOO Conference</a></strong> in Richmond Hill in October.</p>\n<br /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11150/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/dougpete.wordpress.com/11150/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=dougpete.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2477343&#038;post=11150&#038;subd=dougpete&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,NULL),(769,0,0,'It&apos;s time to re-think about education models  #mooc #oped12 http://t.co/qIN4Ja3T','twitter','http://twitter.com/suifaijohnmak/statuses/252048333504389122','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,342,'http://twitter.com/suifaijohnmak/statuses/252048333504389122',NULL,NULL,29,'It&apos;s time to re-think about education models <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23mooc\" title=\"#mooc\" class=\" \">#mooc</a> #<em>oped12</em> <a href=\"http://t.co/qIN4Ja3T\">http://t.co/qIN4Ja3T</a>',1348930203,NULL,NULL,'suifaijohnmak','http://twitter.com/suifaijohnmak','Sat, 29 Sep 2012 14:13:00 +0000',NULL,'oped12 - Twitter Search',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(770,1,0,'English 2.0','Diigo','http://www.scoop.it/t/english-2-0','edubloggers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,30,'<p><strong>Comments:</strong><ul><li>the benefits of